title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a greased pan.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Blend butter, sugar, vanilla, salt and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in sour cream. Add to egg mixture. Fold in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans or into cupcake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cupcakes take 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with Strawberry Butter for a special treat.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Note:
Drain juice on all but peach pie filling.

title: crab muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except muffins (smash together with a fork).
Spread on muffins, then cut into fourths.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze for at least 30 minutes.
When you need them, just put in oven to broil until cheese gets bubbly.

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in cold water in a 4-quart pot.
Add garlic, celery, onion and oil and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 2 hours.
Add water as needed, stirring occasionally. Add salt, pepper, sausage and Cajun seasoning and continue cooking over low heat for about 1 hour.
Serve over a bed of steaming rice and enjoy!

title: chili rellenos
directions: Seed chilies.
Put layer of chilies in greased baking dish, then layer of cheese, layer of chilies, cheese, etc.
Blend milk, flour and eggs in blender.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: peachy pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs (adding egg one at a time and beating well after each egg).
Add vanilla, almond extract, flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add sour cream.
Fold peaches into batter.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes.

title: saralyn's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti until just tender; drain and keep warm.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until lightly browned.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add broth.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Stir in cream and sherry.
Combine 1/2 of the sauce with spaghetti.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
To remaining sauce, add chicken, pimento and almonds; pour on top of spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Brown lightly in moderate oven, 375°, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Stir in flour; mix until it forms a ball.
Beat in eggs with an electric mixer into flour mixture, one at a time.
Press into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses and chop olives fine and mix ingredients together with hands, forming a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Cook bacon, pork chops and sausage. Crumble up bacon and sausage and cut pork chops in small pieces.
Save 2 tablespoons grease from sausage and scramble 6 eggs; put aside.
Saute bell pepper and celery.
Put all ingredients together in large skillet and heat.
Add soy sauce.
Hot peppers are optional.

title: chicken tetrazzini(from rafter's restaurant)
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Remove from bone while warm and cut into cubes.
Cook spaghetti in 1 quart water or chicken stock. Cut onion in pieces and mix with mushrooms and juice.
Mix with drained spaghetti and chicken.
Make white sauce by melting oleo, adding flour and slowly adding milk.
Cut up cheese and add to white sauce.
Stir until melted.
Mix into the chicken and spaghetti.
Pour into baking dish and bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes.

title: peanut streusel pie(peanut butter pie)
directions: Blend peanut butter with confectioners sugar until mealy. Sprinkle two-thirds of mixture over baked pie shell.
Fill with filling and top with whipped cream and rest of streusel.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk; boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop from a spoon on wax paper.

title: kosoff-kennedy cheesecake
directions: Make Praline Crust and chill 15 minutes before using.
In large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat together sour cream, eggs and vanilla until blended.
Pour into chilled Praline Crust.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven on center rack until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Cool, then chill.

title: autumn apple cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg, mixing until well blended; set it aside.
Combine dry ingredients; add combined oil and 3 eggs, mixing until moistened.
Fold in apples and nuts. Reserve 2 1/2 cups batter and pour remaining batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over batter; carefully spoon reserved batter over cream cheese mixture spreading lightly to cover.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan; cool thoroughly.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix flours together with dry milk and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let proof 5 minutes.
Gradually beat into flour mixture along with beef broth.
Will be stiff and hard to mix (may need to use your hands).
Let rest 5 minutes, roll out to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut out dog biscuit shapes.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg glaze.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°; turn off heat leaving biscuits in oven overnight to harden.
Store in airtight container.
Add 1/2 teaspoon garlic or 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese for gourmet dogs.

title: feve la scala
directions: Rinse beans; place in large saucepan.
Add water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Transfer to a bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain beans, reserving 1 1/2 cups of the liquid.

title: southern fried chicken with buttermilk(yields 4 servings)
directions: Mix flour, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper on a plate.
Roll chicken in it to coat.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet over high heat.
When hot, add chicken and brown on all sides, 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add buttermilk to skillet.
Scrape pan to loosen any brown bits.
Return chicken to skillet, skin side up.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until chicken is tender and juices run clear, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, eggs, onions, Parmesan, salt, oregano and milk until blended.
Put in pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: george's green pea salad
directions: Combine ingredients into a medium bowl, but not the cheese; leave in refrigerator for 1 hour and remove when ready to serve. Place lettuce leaves on a platter. Spoon salad onto the leaves and sprinkle grated cheese on top. (For added touch, add ham, cut into small cubes, to the mixed ingredients.)

title: egg custard
directions: Heat milk to boiling.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Pour boiling hot milk into egg and sugar mixture and beat for 1 minute.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes, then 425° for 10 minutes.
Done when knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pie.

title: rita's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Boil 15 minutes.

title: baked beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle Season-All salt on both sides of brisket. Put in pan with fat side up. Cover with foil. Bake in oven at 450° for 45 minutes. Pour 10 oz. of Coke over the top. Sprinkle 1 pkg. of onion soup mix over brisket, cover and bake at 250° for 2 hours. Remove from oven, let cool, slice, and reheat.

title: white sauce pasta
directions: Boil water. Add penne. Cook 8 to 10 minutes in salted water with a little olive oil. Drain. (DO NOT RINSE.)

title: green beans provencale
directions: Wash beans; drain.
Trim ends, cut on diagonal in 1-inch pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a medium skillet.
Cook, covered, over low heat, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender.
Serves 4.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Put flour in bowl and add salt.
Cut up chicken.
Fry only 5 pieces.
Put other in refrigerator.
Roll chicken in flour.
Put 1/4 cup fat in frying pan and heat.
Place chicken in hot fat; brown both sides.
Take pan off heat.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup water; cover frying pan.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: senator's bean soup
directions: Heat soups and water.
Add garlic, crushed.
Add parsley. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add ham and heat thoroughly.
Serve with celery sticks, carrot sticks, green onions and radishes.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool until set and beat until smooth.
Add flavor to whipped cream and fold in marshmallows, then add peaches.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Boil macaroni; rinse and drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Chill 6 to 8 hours prior to serving.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix sausage and Bisquick.
Add cheese and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Put ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan in order given. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Beat well.
Pour into hot greased skillet.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: peanut butter and jelly thumbs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: bloodhounds
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Season with spices.
Add veggies and one jar of pizza sauce.
Simmer until veggies are tender. Split buns.
Cover buns with meat mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon pizza sauce to each filled bun.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Makes approximately 30 hounds, depending on how much meat is used on each bun.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pans. Sift together dry ingredients. Blend other ingredients. Fold in bananas and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Thoroughly mix above ingredients.
Serve on salad greens or a special sauce for hamburger.

title: cheese ball spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except bell pepper and onion.
Blend in blender; then add onion and bell pepper.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and lemon juice.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add bananas.
Sift salt, flour, soda and baking powder, add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture.
Fold in nuts. Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
(I put a sheet of wax paper in the bottom of pans.)
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: scented christmas ornaments
directions: Start by twisting off the two claws.

title: hot and spicy spanish sauce
directions: Saute bell peppers and onion in butter.
Add all other ingredients; simmer until well blended, 15 to 20 minutes.
Can serve as a Spanish omelette or with Italian sausage over rice.

title: libby's famous pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool; garnish, if desired, with whipped topping.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line large casserole or roasting pan with bread.
Slightly beat eggs and combine with milk.
Pour over bread.
Mix cheese and bacon together and put on top of egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Prepare the night before and put in oven upon rising.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cook artichokes (if frozen) according to directions.
Cut up in small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and garlic powder.
Blend in artichokes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve at once with snack crackers.

title: traverse city cherry pie
directions: Mix cherries together with sugar, flour, extract and salt. Pour into pastry shell.
Dot with butter.
Place lattice top on, sealing with water and crimping edges high.
Bake at 350° until brown or done.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; add bourbon and corn syrup and mix.
Grease hands and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and refrigerate.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: *If using plain flour add 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and pinch of salt.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: moonshine cake(never refrigerate any of this cake)
directions: Put in saucepan and melt butter and sugar; add milk.
Cook slowly, stirring the whole time.
Let bubble for 1 minute.
Then take off stove and beat.
Add hot mixture to 1 1/2 cups or more powdered sugar a little at a time.
This makes enough for 3 cakes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Place rest of ingredients except nuts into blender and blend until smooth.
Pour over flour mixture and add nuts.
Mix lightly until blended.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in well greased loaf pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.
Freezes well.

title: bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk, egg, molasses and combined dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake about 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend first four ingredients; add rhubarb and eggs and pour over rhubarb in pie shell.
Top with pastry cover.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.
Add chicken that has been cooked and cut into bite size pieces.
Put into a casserole and top with biscuits. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Leftover turkey can be used in place of chicken.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Let first 3 ingredients stand 7 days.
Drain and pour off liquid.
Add boiling water and alum.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain; pour off liquid.
Make syrup of vinegar and sugar.
Boil and pour over cucumbers.
Continue this for 4 days.
Add spices to taste. Can and seal.

title: creole sausage jambalaya
directions: Preheat fat in iron skillet or Dutch oven.
Add 1 cup water, crumbled sausage, cooked slowly, until brown, stirring occasionally.
Add onion, celery, tomatoes, bell peppers and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
Add rice and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook, covered, over very low heat 30 minutes or until water has cooked out.
Stir occasionally.
Add thyme, parsley and onion.
Stir mixture well.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Make meatballs of ground beef, ginger and salt.
Dip in beaten egg and flour.
Saute in oil.
Mix vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and juice from pineapple plus water to make 1 cup.
Boil approximately 3 minutes.
Add meatballs, green peppers and pineapple chunks in separate piles in frypan.
Coat with sauce. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: great pound cake
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and the other ingredients.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour or until golden brown, at 350°.

title: banana slush
directions: Heat sugar in water until dissolved.
Add orange juice and set aside to cool.
Mash bananas.
Add bananas, pineapple juice and lemon juice to mixture.
Freeze mixture 8 to 10 hours.
Mix 1/2 slush and 1/2 7-Up in blender.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and crumbs.
Put into pie plate and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Mash cream cheese with powdered sugar; cream well.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Put into cooled crust.
Top with cherry pie filling mixed with 1/4 cup sugar and almond extract. Chill.

title: lo-cal potato salad(makes 4 cups)
directions: Put the potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to low and simmer for about 10 minutes or until just fork-tender.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough flour to make a medium batter.
Drop in hot grease and cook on both sides.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Mix last three ingredients. Grease one cookie sheet.
Spread with spaghetti. Sprinkle ground beef over spaghetti.
Cover with pizza sauce mixture. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix together in greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Melt butter in frying pan and scramble eggs.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart rectangular casserole.
Place sausage on the eggs and top with mushrooms.
Combine soup and sherry in saucepan and warm on top of stove.
Spread warm mixture on top of mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
While your family opens presents on Christmas morning, bake covered casserole in 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: aunt bobbie's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cook noodles until done; drain. Don't overcook.
Add in bowl or pan the chicken soup.
Drain peas and carrots; add to soup.
Add cheese; mix well.
Add enough broth to make soupy.
Mix chicken, noodles and soup mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine flour, oats, buttermilk powder, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in mixing bowl and stir together.
Combine water, egg and oil; pour into dry mixture and beat smooth, but do not overbeat.
Heat griddle or frying pan to medium or medium-high. Grease pan with pastry brush and shortening.
For each pancake, pour 1/4 cup batter onto pan.
Cook pancakes until puffed (bubbled on top) and dry around edges.
Turn and cook on other side until golden brown.
Serve with applesauce or butter and syrup.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour or longer at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peg's breakfast pizza
directions: Brown meat and spoon over prepared crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over potatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: honey-oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and honey. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about two inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about five dozen cookies.

title: one dish stroganoff
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook beef until brown; drain. Stir in water, undrained mushrooms, parsley, catsup, bouillon cube and pepper. Stir in uncooked noodles. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat, then simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until noodles are tender. Stir occasionally.
Stir together dip and flour, then stir into meat mixture in saucepan. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, then cook and stir for 1 minute more.

title: finnish beef stew
directions: * Meat should be in approximately 1-inch cubes.

title: crock-pot hot dogs
directions: In crock-pot, melt jelly and mustard together on medium heat. Once jelly and mustard are blended, add hot dogs and cook for 20 minutes before serving.
Serve hot.
Leave crock-pot on low heat.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic, celery and pepper in oil. Brown beef; drain. Combine all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir ingredients together and cook over medium-heat until peanuts start popping and liquid looks the color of light honey. Do not overcook.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon soda and pour on buttered surface.
To prepare butter surface, butter aluminum foil heavily and place on cookie sheet.
When candy is cold, break into pieces.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda; set aside for 20 minutes.
Mix buttermilk with syrup, sugar and salt; bring to a boil.
Add butter; let boil until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cool water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool 30 minutes.
Beat until creamy.
Add pecans and pour into greased pan.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large soup pot, render bacon and lard together.
Then sweat the vegetables and thyme in this fat without taking any color.
Stir in the flour to make a smooth paste.
Slowly add the clam juice, stirring constantly.
Add the milk, cream and potatoes and simmer slowly until potatoes are tender.
Add the clams and cook another 2 minutes.
Adjust seasoning with white pepper, but use salt sparingly.
Remove soup from the heat and melt pads of butter on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers or buttered toast.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken slowly.
Debone and cut in bite-size pieces. Cook and drain broccoli.
Place broccoli in bottom of shallow 2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken.
Mix soup and milk, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour on top of broccoli and chicken.
Top with shredded cheese and a thin layer of fine bread crumbs that have been sauteed in butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: what's for supper casserole
directions: Fry meat until done.
Remove from heat.
Grease large casserole dish.
Layer macaroni, meat, tomato sauce and cheese for at least 2 layers of each, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with salad, bread and ice tea and you have what's for supper.

title: aunt pearl's marinated slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over cabbage in large bowl.
Combine vinegar, oil, celery seed, dry mustard and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and continue to boil for 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix with hands.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix thoroughly and form into a ball.
Sprinkle with pecans, chives and paprika.
Can substitute chicken or ham.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Drain pineapple and place juice in pan with vinegar, sugar, salt and soy sauce.
Bring to boil; add pineapple and green pepper.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed in small amount of water.

title: quick applesauce raisin bread
directions: Combine eggs, applesauce, melted butter and both sugars.
Mix well by hand.
Mix in dry ingredients. Pour into well-greased fluted mold (1 quart) or 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven about 1 hour.
Cool.
Frost with simple confectioners sugar frosting, if desired.
Slices best second day.

title: impossible tuna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Mix tuna, cheese, onion and pimento.
Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 35 or 40 minutes.

title: cream pudding
directions: Beat eggs and milk until well blended. Add sugar and cornstarch.
Mix all ingredients together. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat after it boils and let cool.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Excellent for cream pies, cream puff filling or for just pudding!

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mandarin oranges (add them last). Bake in 3 layer pans or 9 x 13 pan 25 minutes at 325°.

title: mushroom biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter. Add seasonings and set aside to cool slightly.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender.
Add milk and then stir in mushroom mixture.
Drop from a spoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes, until browned.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend in order the sugar, salt, flour, egg, fruit juice, vinegar, lemon juice and butter.
Add bananas, pineapple, pears, cherries and whipped cream.
After blending all ingredients together, freeze.

title: taco salad
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Brown ground beef.
Spread crushed Doritos in bottom of cake pan, spread ground beef on top of Doritos.
Layer cheese on ground beef.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted.
Spread half of taco sauce on cheese.
Put on a layer of lettuce and a layer of tomatoes.
Pour remaining sauce on top.

title: sausage and egg strata
directions: Layer bread, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix eggs and 1 cup milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix soup, mushrooms and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour mixture over refrigerated bread mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: maryland crab imperial
directions: Mix together flour, mustard, salt and red pepper.
Melt butter; add dry ingredients and 1/2 cup milk.
Let come to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Add this mixture to sauce and continue to cook (slowly) for another 5 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons sherry, if desired.
Combine crab and sauce thoroughly.
Serve in shells.
Serves 4 people.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onions and garlic in bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes and green chiles and cook until thick.
Add 1 cup sour cream and grated cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Soften tortillas for a few seconds in hot oil and drain.
In a casserole dish, alternate tortillas and sauce.
Bake 30 minutes.
Garnish with dabs of sour cream before serving.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing, macaroni, tuna, celery, green pepper, onion and pimiento.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate. Serve on top of lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1 cup sugar, almond extract, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Heat in oven while preparing shortcake.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder in 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Add milk and egg at once; stir just until flour is moistened.
Spread dough over hot peaches.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 or 50 minutes.
Cool and top with whip cream or ice cream.

title: iroquoian wild lettuce salad with vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine the greens together in a large wooden salad bowl. Toss with Vinaigrette Dressing (recipe follows).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy graham squares
directions: Line jellyroll pan or cookie sheet with crackers. Melt margarine and add sugar. Bring to a rolling boil. Add nuts. Spread over crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix and heat until ingredients form a ball.
Add a touch of food coloring if desired.
Stir in airtight container.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all together with an electric mixer. Place in a microwave dish that has a lid.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Serve with large Fritos chips.

title: toffee crackers
directions: Take a cookie sheet.
Use no oil.
Place crackers in a row.
In a pan, melt butter, about 1/2 stick.
Pour over crackers.
Next, sprinkle brown sugar over crackers.
Be generous.
Place in oven at 300° until sugar has glazed look.
Cool and eat.

title: one pan spanish noodles
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Saute onion, parsley and beef in bacon drippings until beef is browned.
Skim off fat.
Add tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Bring to a full boil. Add noodles a few at a time.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender.
Transfer to serving dish and sprinkle bacon on top.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine mushroom soup, chicken soup, rice, hamburger, taco sauce, onion, green pepper, Doritos and Cheddar cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.

title: creamsicle punch
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, beat eggs with honey until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in juices.
Cover; refrigerate. Just before serving, spoon ice cream into large punch bowl.
Add juice mixture, then soft drink.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 14 (16 ounce) servings.

title: snicker bar cookies
directions: Wrap peanut butter cookie dough completely around a snicker bite.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 minutes at 325 degrees. Let cool on sheet before removing them.

title: cookies
directions: Cook pitted dates, water and sugar until thick, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
In a large bowl, put lard, brown sugar, white sugar, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix and then add beaten eggs.
If too dry to handle, add just a tiny bit of water.
Make in about 3 balls, then roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with date mixture and then roll up like cinnamon rolls.
Put in refrigerator until it is well chilled.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed citrus coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs; blend in salad oil and evaporated milk.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture, blending well. Stir in rinds and poppy seed.
Turn into greased and floured 3-quart Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on wire rack.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Heat soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms and preferred sauce.
Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Add broccoli to soup mixture; serve warm.

title: charcoaled hamburger
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan and mix thoroughly.
Make into hamburger patties and charcoal.
Mop with Barbecue Sauce.

title: macaroni with vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, cook broccoli, mushrooms, carrot, onion and garlic in margarine until tender-crisp.
Stir in tomato.
Cook 2 minutes; toss vegetable mixture with hot macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: meatballs in cocktail sauce
directions: Shape meat into 1-inch balls.
Place on a jelly roll pan. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Heat until thickened.
Add sliced apples and simmer until partially cooked. Pour into unbaked pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or cover apples with crumb crust granola or eat alone.

title: graham cracker cakes
directions: Split grahams in half.
Layer grahams with strawberry jam and stack (about 5 crackers).
Cover with Cool Whip or whipping cream. Refrigerate overnight.

title: kibbles and bits
directions: Melt chips, oleo, and peanut butter. Pour over cereal.
Stir till well coated. Pour into a brown paper bag that has powdered sugar in it. Shake well. Spread on cookie sheet to dry. Store in container.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Combine remaining ingredients and pour mixture over meat.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garden salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes in metal pan.

title: dairy treat
directions: Before serving, spread Cool Whip over dessert; crush candy bars and sprinkle over top.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions and butter in skillet about 15 minutes, covered. Uncover and add salt, sugar and flour.
Stir well.
Cook about 2 minutes over low heat.

title: noodles with chicken livers
directions: Blanch beans for 1 minute.
Remove beans from water and add pasta to the same boiling water.
Cook al dente; drain.
Heat butter and saute livers to brown on outside.
Add mushrooms and vinegar.
Increase heat to reduce liquid.
Season, then pour in stock, then reduce by half.
Stir in beans, pasta and parsley.

title: thin swedish pancakes
directions: Mix eggs and 1 cup milk.
Add wheat flour and salt and beat until it forms a smooth batter.
Add another 1 cup milk and melted butter.
Heat a pancake pan or frying pan.
Pour a thin layer of batter in the pan.
Bake until brown on one side.
Turn over and bake on the other side.
It may be necessary to melt a little butter in the pan for the first pancake.
Serve the pancakes with jam, lingonberries, fruit sauce or fresh berries.
Small blini-sized pancakes made in the same manner on a special griddle are called "plattar."
Makes 4 servings.
This is a favorite of Prince Bertil of Sweden.

title: fancy liqueur chocolates
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.
In the saucepan, combine sugar, water, cream and light corn syrup.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon to dissolve sugar.
This should take 5 to 6 minutes. Avoid splashing mixture on sides of pan.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together and fold in with all other ingredients.
Put in any shape mold.
Freeze.

title: mimosa salad
directions: In a salad bowl, mix
together	the
cream, lemon juice and seasonings.
Wash and dry lettuce leaves.
Peel the orange and cut
into
thin
slices.
Wash
grapes.
Peel
and	slice banana. Place the lettuce leaves,
orange,	grapes and banana in salad bowl on top of
dressing.
Toss
just
before serving and garnish with sliced egg.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Mix together oleo, Crisco, sugar, egg yolk, cake flour, buttermilk, soda, coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites and mix well. Bake in three 8-inch cake pans for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rich and krispy cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients in mixer.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll in balls and flatten.
Bake at 325°.
Watch closely, as they brown very easily.

title: "robert redford" dessert
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cheese soften then beat with mixer.
Add milk and spices. Add more milk if you want it thinner.
Add the shrimp at end and mix gently in with a fork.

title: wine chicken
directions: Place in baking pan and cover with chicken soup, Swiss cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour wine and butter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hearty lima bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Cook beans in water about one hour.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry in large skillet until crisp.
Add vegetables to bacon and cook until limp, about five minutes.
Add vegetables to beans.

title: pennsylvania-style sugar cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until top of sugar cakes are lightly browned.

title: crunchy corn casserole
directions: Saute green pepper in butter or margarine until soft.
Add corn, pimento, egg and half a can of fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until firm.
Sprinkle rest of onions on top and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: homestyle kosher dills
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut off ends and pack in quart jars.
Add dill, hot pepper and cloves.
Bring to a boil the water, vinegar and salt.
Pour hot solution over cucumbers and seal jars. Pickles will be ready in 3 to 4 weeks.
Makes 4 or 5 quarts.

title: jello and cream cheese salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to package.
Mix cream cheese and milk together.
Stir into Jell-O.
Mix one cup of nuts into Jell-O. Refrigerate and let set.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of nuts on top.

title: crock-pot  dip
directions: Brown meat. Drain.
In crock-pot, melt cheese and add meat. Keep warm and serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together in boiler.
Cook until thick and spread on yellow cake mix (I use a lite cake mix).

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix good and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes two 6-inch logs or 1 big ball.
Roll in chili powder.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar. Add eggs, vanilla. Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, and baking powder. Add to first mixture. Stir in oatmeal and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown; stir continually.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/4 cream mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle caramel on each pie. Sprinkle coconut evenly over each pie.
Repeat layers until all is used.
Freeze.
Take out 1 hour before time to serve.
Enjoy.

title: pulled mints(cateress - glenda lindstrom)
directions: Dissolve sugar and water and bring to a boil.
Be sure to use a heavy pan.
Take a fork that has been wrapped with paper towels and wipe the sides of the pan.
This cleans off any sugar crystals that are on the sides of the pan.
Put the lid on and cook for about 2 minutes; add butter and cook until the candy thermometer reaches about 254° to 256°.
Remove from heat and pour onto a buttered marble top.
(Do not scrape pan.)
When cool enough to handle, add 4 drops of oil of peppermint and coloring.
Pull until the candy loses its gloss and holds its shape.
Pull into a one-inch rope and cut into bite size pieces with scissors.
After cutting, leave out for a couple of hours.
When they don't stick together anymore, put in cookie tin until softened, which will take from 2 hours to 2 days.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute green onions and celery in butter until soft.
Add flour and blend.
Add cream and blend.
Remove from heat and add crabmeat.
Add grated cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple, save syrup. Mix cheese, nuts, marshmallows, and grapes. Heat 1 cup of syrup with sugar, beaten egg, and cornstarch. Stir and cook until it thickens. Cool. Pour over first pineapple mixture, stirring until coated. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chalupas
directions: This recipe is for one serving.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt margarine and combine with sugar and beaten eggs.
Add pineapple and bread cubes.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafers.
Slice half of the ice cream and put on top of vanilla wafers.
Melt, in double boiler, the chocolate chips, milk and marshmallows.
Pour 1/2 over ice cream.
Put another layer of vanilla wafers, ice cream and chocolate mixture.
Top with nuts.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: In medium mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients in four additions, alternately with water until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Two teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: corn muffin casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased 9 X 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: quick meat pie
directions: In frypan, brown beef and onions.
Add salt.
Drain fat.
Add soup, green beans and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Drop potatoes in mounds onto hot meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker pudding #2
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar and crumbs.
Add egg yolks and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; beat again, gradually adding 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into pudding.
Chill.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: ham and egg quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle hard-cooked eggs in bottom of pie crust.
Top with ham and cheeses.
Combine beaten eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over filling.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet until mixture is set, about 35 minutes.
Let stand before serving.

title: devil's food chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir in cocoa mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Make a batter with the eggs, basil, salt and pepper.
Peel and slice the eggplant.
Thin slices are preferable.
Dip each slice in the batter and drop into heated oil in frying pan.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: better than pie apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon, a little at a time.
Fold in chopped apples and nuts.

title: waffle mix
directions: Beat egg yolks and whites separately.
Mix butter, egg yolk, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Combine well.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in preheated waffle iron.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Melt butter with peanut butter in microwave; mix and set aside.
Mix oatmeal, 1 cup
flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add peanut butter mixture; mix until crumbly. Spread 2/3 mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle semi-sweet chips over cooked mixture. Drizzle warm fudge topping mixed with 3 tablespoons flour and top with the remaining 1/3 of left over mixture.
Bake 20 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off grease.
Add taco mix with about 2 tablespoons water.
Cook slowly about 15 minutes.
Mix in a large bowl, tomatoes, lettuce, cheese, hamburger and chopped onions.

title: sweet potatoes for company
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, granulated sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/2 cup melted butter and pecans; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli en casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in hot water.
Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and add dressing on top and return to oven and bake until brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet. Drain off fat. Add tomatoes, onion and chiles and simmer, covered, approximately 20 minutes.
In a large bowl, tear lettuce into bite size pieces. Add Fritos and cheese. When ready to eat, add hot hamburger mixture and toss. Top with fresh tomatoes, green onions and taco sauce.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Marinate together the water, soy sauce, white wine and cornstarch.
Rinse and pat dry chicken, then cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Add to marinade; stir to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes. Drain chicken and save marinade.
Preheat wok on high heat; add oil.
Stir green onions, mushrooms and garlic 1 to 2 minutes until tender.
Add chicken and cook 2 to 3 minutes until chicken is no longer pink. Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, combine everything but the vanilla.

Stir with a wooden spoon, scraping the sides and bottom of the pan, breaking up lumps. When mixture is smooth and beginning to thicken, bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Cool or chill for 1 hour.

title: twinkies
directions: Bake in 2 flat cookie sheets.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and put into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together; pour into greased pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: orange vinaigrette dressing
directions: In a small bowl, beat together orange juice, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
It makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: russian cheesecake with chocolate glaze
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Cook lemon rind in sugar water until tender.
Toast almonds lightly in butter.
Mix all ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Blend in almonds and mix throughout.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix the ingredients; pour into large casserole.
Top with 2 strips bacon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Very good with Charolais steak and Italian or French bread loaves heated in foil with butter and garlic salt.

title: quick carrot soup
directions: Cook onion for 1 minute.
Add evaporated milk, skim milk, carrots and seasoning.
Make paste of cornstarch and water, stirring constantly.
When soup begins to simmer, cook over low heat about 15 minutes, stir often.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients.
Cut the stems off mushrooms, brush with butter and stuff with the spinach mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: frozen peach salad
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple, extract and pie filling.
Pour into loaf pan; mold and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar. Add dry ingredients, 1 cup oil and pumpkin. Mix well. Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yams deluxe
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Spread on bottom of a 9-inch baking dish. Mix yams and seasonings.
Drop in 8 portions on sugar mixture.
Top with marshmallows and nuts.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream well the cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar. Add milk a little at a time to break up any lumps and blend well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in the pie shell and freeze.

title: curried fruit(servings:  4)
directions: Spread fruit in a 2-quart casserole, flat.
Melt butter; blend in brown sugar and curry.
Spoon over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla snacks
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together until smooth.
Mix in thoroughly the chopped up jalapenos.
Add just a tad bit of jalapeno juice if you want a hot taste.
Lay a tortilla flat and spread mixture evenly, roll up and cut up into bite-size pieces. Refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat 10 minutes, then spread over crust.
Add bananas.
Cover bananas with pineapple.
Over pineapple, spread Dream Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.

title: 1 - 2 - 3 - 4 cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure creamed shortening and vanilla.
Add sugar and creamed mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour alternately with the milk.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: simple acorn squash casserole(clara deariso's)
directions: Split
acorn
squash in halves or quarter it.
Sprinkle brown sugar
on it, then dot with butter or pour melted butter over it. Bake
at 350° to 375° until tender.
Mash up mixture in shell and serve.

title: cherry cheese cream tarts
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, cream cheese, vanilla, and lemon juice until smooth.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meat loaf mix into the ground beef.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Fry in skillet until brown and done.
Remove from skillet. Combine ketchup, jelly and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan.
Cook on low until jelly is dissolved.
Add meatballs in the saucepan and simmer.
Serve in crock-pot or saucepan.
Remove with toothpicks.

title: chinese pineapple chicken
directions: Brown chicken in vegetable oil and salt.
Add garlic, chopped onion and ginger; saute.
Drain pineapple; save juice.
Mix 1/4 cup juice and cornstarch.
Mix remaining juice with chicken broth, soy sauce, honey and cinnamon.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer for 30 minutes, covered, until chicken is tender.
Stir cornstarch mixture in and cook until thickened.
Add pineapple.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add onion, milk, cheese and 4 Tbsp. melted butter.
Toss bread cubes in remaining 2 Tbsp. butter.
Put spinach mixture in buttered casserole.
Arrange bread cubes on top.
Bake 25 minutes uncovered at 375 degrees.

title: broccoli pudding(for 12 or more)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, eggs, soup and onion.
Add cooked broccoli.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Cook 1 hour, until golden and bubbly.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Marinate as long as possible.
Makes enough for 6 chops. Grill according to thickness.

title: grandma's "panny cakes"
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Beat eggs lightly; stir in milk.
Then add melted shortening.
Add liquids all at once to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
(A spoon may be used.)
Bake on hot griddle until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Sift cocoa and powdered sugar into a bowl.
Stir in bourbon which has been combined with syrup; mix well.
Add crumbs and nuts; mix well again.
Roll into small balls about 3/4 inch in diameter.
Drop into a bowl of powdered sugar; roll around to coat on all sides.
Allow to dry several hours before using.
These may be prepared ahead of time and will freeze well.
Keep in airtight container.
Before serving, put an additional small amount of powdered sugar into container and shake.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Grease 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Line bottom with bread (cut off crust). Place sausage on bread.
Pour egg mixture on sausage.
Place cheese on egg mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole #1
directions: Melt butter in dish; stir in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir twice while baking gently so as not to break up vegetables.
Can be cooked successfully in a microwave oven on High for about 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Make cake according to box directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool completely.
Cut half the cake into large chunks and place them into bottom of glass bowl.
Pour 1/4 cup Kahlua over cake pieces and pat down.
Mix chocolate pudding according to package and pour half over the cake.
Spread half the Cool Whip over pudding and cake.
Crush candy bars and sprinkle half over Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used. Top final layer of Cool Whip and candy with sprinkles and maraschino cherries.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Microwave sausage; drain and set aside to cool.
Grease large pan or cookie sheet.
Flatten crescent rolls into cookie sheet making sure you squeeze together at perforations.
Mix eggs, onions, mushrooms, cheese and milk in large bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble sausage into bowl and stir.
Pour mixture over crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Mix pecans and Bugles.
Chip butter over top.
Cook in oven about 45 minutes at 350°.
Watch closely and stir every 5 to 10 minutes.

title: carol's dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and dressing mix with electric mixer.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Stir in sour cream.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving with vegetables or chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown chicken as for frying, then place in baking dish. Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil, add eggs. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add to sugar oil and eggs, fold in carrots. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barb's cheesecake
directions: In a bowl, combine contents of crust mix packages, butter and sugar.
Press onto the bottom of an ungreased 10-inch spring-form pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Gradually beat in remaining milk.	Add contents of filling mix packages; beat until smooth.
Beat on medium for 3 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.	Pour over crust.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Top with pie filling.
Remove sides of pan before serving.

title: pie crust no. 2
directions: In large mixing bowl, add salt to flour, then cut shortening into flour until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Add water, mixing until above mixture sticks together.
Divide into 6 portions; roll out dough to fit pie tin.
Place wax paper over 1/2 of crust, then fold.
Place more wax paper on this and fold into quarters.
Place in freezer bag with wax paper or Glad Wrap between crusts.
Use as needed - freeze extras.
This recipe makes 2 double crust cobblers.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except sugar.
Roll mixture into walnut size balls; coat in powdered sugar.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: quick crab casserole
directions: Saute vegetables
in
stick	oleo
until tender; add crabmeat.
Soak
bread
in	enough	milk to soften completely. Break into pieces
and add to crab mixture.
Stir well and add seasonings.
Place	in 1 1/2 quart greased casserole; add milk to moisten.
Run
knife
up and down until absorbed.
Dot with oleo and cover
with bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta rice
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, saute onion in butter until tender. Transfer to a large bowl.
Stir in the next eight ingredients.
Divide between two ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Stir two cups of water into each pan.

title: pita bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, sugar and flour to water and stir.
Knead lightly and let dough rise 1 hour in a warm place.
Knead dough again.
Divide dough into 8 equal parts.
Form each part into a ball and place on floured waxed paper.
Let balls rise for 30 minutes.
Roll each ball on floured paper into a circle about 4 inches in diameter.
Flour cookie sheet.
Arrange 4 circles on pan.
Preheat oven to 500° for 15 minutes and bake for 3 minutes.
Bread will look puffed in the middle and the outside will be off-white with brown spots.
After cooling, pita should be tightly wrapped to prevent drying.
Make half moon; slice along edge of bread into center to form opening.

title: killed lettuce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over leaf lettuce.
Good.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter.
Mix cornstarch, salt and sugar into orange juice; add this mixture to the melted butter, slowly, stirring constantly.
When thickened, pour over cooked carrots; top with chopped parsley, for garnish.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in 1/2 cup milk in top of double boiler. Let cool, stirring occasionally.
When cold, whip the whipping cream until stiff and fold into the marshmallow mixture.
Fold in grated chocolate.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine soup.
Slowly stir in water and milk.
Stir in sherry and half of cheese cubes.
When very hot, but not boiling, add chopped parsley, almonds and the rest of cheese cubes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate cherry chip cake
directions: Put dry cake mix in a large bowl.
Cook pudding and add warm pudding to the dry cake mix.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake with nuts and chocolate chips (as much as desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate skillet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt together in bowl and set aside.
In large saucepan or big skillet combine: Oleo, water, shortening and cocoa.

title: creamy crock-pot potatoes
directions: Toss potato slices in 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar; drain.
Put half of potatoes in greased crock-pot.
Top with half of the onion slices, flour, salt and pepper.
Add remaining sliced potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle remaining flour, salt and pepper.
Add butter and undiluted soup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 7 hours or on high for 2 to 3 hours.
Add cheese 30 minutes before serving.
Recipe may be doubled for a 5-quart crock-pot.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings in pan. Dip chicken in butter and roll in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dottie weber's easy pate
directions: Grease a loaf pan (7 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch) or a 3 1/2-cup mold.

title: molded salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add cream cheese broken in pieces; add pineapple with the juice.
Add whipped cream and beat.
Pour into bottom of mold. Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup hot water; add 1 cup cold water. Let set until firm, then beat and pour over the first mixture and let set until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: outreach supper
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add meat, soup and vegetables.
Heat together.
I learned to make this while shopping for the Outreach Pantry.
You can use any kind of meat, noodles, soup and vegetables.

title: cranberry mold(excellent for holiday meals)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup (if necessary) to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Cool and gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partly set.
Blend pineapple and cranberry sauce into jello.
Put in flat dish (such as a square or rectangle casserole dish).
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold cream cheese into Dream Whip.
Spread over gelatin and top with nuts.

title: honey baked beans
directions: Soak washed beans in 4 cups warm water for 3 hours.
Cook on low heat in tightly covered saucepan for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not allow to boil.
Drain the beans, saving the water.
Place salt pork in the bottom of bean pot and add beans.
Cover with mixture made of the bean water, onion, ginger, honey, salt and mustard. Add boiling water, if needed.
Place small pieces of salt pork on top.
Cover pot and bake in slow oven about 6 hours.
Uncover bean pot during the last hour of baking.
If the beans become too dry, add a little boiling water.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Blend cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Mixture should be creamy.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Let cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small bite-size balls.
At Easter, shape into egg shapes.
Dip in chocolate.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes. Delicious!

title: orange marmalade
directions: Quarter oranges and put in food processor. Measure the pulp and put in a pot. Add half as much water as pulp and bring the mixture to a boil
for 15 minutes. Allow to cool and save overnight (does not need to be refrigerated).

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Drain and break bacon into small pieces. Stir in large saucepan with clam juice, potatoes and water.
Cook, uncovered, until potatoes are tender (about 10 minutes).
Add clams, milk and seasonings and heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Fold in 1 cup chopped nuts.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff and fold in. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown bacon and remove from pan.
In bacon drippings, add onion and green pepper.
Brown lightly.
Add tomatoes, 1/2 cup water, chili powder, garlic, salt, pepper and crumbled bacon. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb-butterscotch upside-down cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg yolks and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add vanilla to milk, then add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and sprinkle with brown sugar evenly over it, then spread with rhubarb and cover with cake batter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before inverting on large platter.
Serve with scoop of whipped cream.

title: chinese style ground beef casserole
directions: Thaw frozen peas.
Brown meat in skillet until crumbly.
In casserole dish, place meat.
Arrange peas over meat.
Add celery over peas.
Mix and add soup, cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Pour liquid mixture over other ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle noodles or chips over top.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: that's good peaches - crock-pot style
directions: Spray crock-pot with nonstick spray.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in peaches and pour in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 6.

title: mom's moist carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Blend in combined dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make sauce of margarine, flour, broth, milk and cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed; bake and refrigerate. Combine powdered sugar, butter, liquor and food coloring.
Spread over baked and cooled brownie mix.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: ground meat and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, pour into casserole dish or small roaster.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice in usual manner; set aside.
Soften both jars of Cheez Whiz by placing in the microwave.
In a mixing bowl, combine thawed broccoli, rice and softened Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dilly mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain.
Mash with remaining ingredients.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dad's microwave grilled cheese
directions: Toast bread in toaster. Then put toasted bread on plate and place cheese on one slice of the bread.
Cover with other slice of toasted bread.
Place in microwave for 15 to 20 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Yields 1 serving.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Add dry ingredients in order given.
Mix on low speed, adding extra flour so as to keep the bowl clean around the edges.
Mix on medium (2) speed 6 minutes.
Use like any yeast dough for various rolls.
Bake at 325° in convection oven.
Makes 24 pounds dough.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with fork.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 7 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk; add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into buttered baking dish (8 x 10-inch pan). Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter; blend in sugar and flour.
Stir in milk; mix smooth.
Add eggs and baking powder.
Fold in corn.
Turn into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jacobs' taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain; add taco seasoning mix and follow directions.
Layer lettuce in bottom of large bowl or you may use taco salad bowls.
If you use taco salad bowls, first follow directions and then layer lettuce in bottom.
Add ground beef, kidney beans, Fritos, tomato, onion and cheese.
Top with salad dressing and enjoy.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oil in skillet; stir-fry chicken for 2 minutes.
Add peppers, onion and cilantro.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in beans; set aside.

title: broccoli and potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes. Make cheese sauce; melt butter. Add flour, stir until blended. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly over medium heat. Add red pepper and salt. Add cheese slices; stir until melted over medium heat. Pour water from potatoes. Add broccoli. Pour cheese sauce over potatoes and broccoli. Mix well. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Sauce should bubble to the top.

title: date bars
directions: Boil dates, sugar and water.
Make a layer of dough, layer of date mixture and layer of dough.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Mix in bowl the sugar, cocoa and beaten eggs.
Pour the melted margarine into the mixture.
Add flour, vanilla and chopped nuts.
When blended, pour into floured pan (the one you melted the margarine in).
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Place large marshmallows 1 inch apart on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes more.
Remove from oven and press marshmallows flat with fork.
When cool, frost.

title: tomato lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Lay flat on foil to cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, heat oil.
Add onion; cook, stirring frequently, until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring to break up tomatoes; set aside.
In bowl, stir together Ricotta cheese, spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
In bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish, spread 3/4 cup tomato mixture.
Spread about 1/3 cup cheese filling on each noodle to within 1-inch of ends; roll up.
Place roll-ups, seam side down, in prepared dish; top with remaining tomatoes.
Cover; bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese; continue baking until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cowboy biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add 3/4 cup milk and knead to a smooth dough; roll out and cut biscuits.
Brush biscuits with remaining milk.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: low calorie fruit salad
directions: Drain all cans of fruits and use 2 cups of drained juices to mix with box of vanilla pudding.
Cook on medium heat until thick. (If you do not get 2 cups of juice from drained fruits, you may add water to make up the difference.)
Let pudding cool.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water and oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add Jell-O and strawberries.
Beat 2 minutes or until well mixed. Pour in cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: apple-cheddar quiche
directions: Cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in crushed crackers and nuts.
Press mixture into a 9-inch pie plate, forming a crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: finger salad
directions: Roll crescent rolls flat and bake (follow directions on package) in 9 x 12 pan.
Mix cream cheese, dry salad mix and mayonnaise.
Spread evenly on bread.
Cut into squares.
Add vegetables and cheese.
Mix cream cheese, dry salad mix and mayonnaise hours earlier so it can season.

title: nacho dip
directions: Blend all together.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese and tomatoes.
Use dip with favorite kind of nacho chips.

title: eggs and cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add flour and baking powder.
Add all cheeses and chopped green chilies.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in baking pan; leave enough in pan to coat well.
Pour the remainder into the egg mixture.
Pour in the pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°. This can be made the night before.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix everything together and pour over potatoes.

title: cynthia's cherry cake
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, water, almond extract and instant vanilla pudding.
Cool in refrigerator while cutting cake into small pieces.
Remove pudding mixture from refrigerator and add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Layer in 2 layers the cut up cake, cream mixture and cherry filling.
Chill and serve.

title: double crust apple pie
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour on bottom crust.
Peel and slice apples very thin.
Pile in crust and cover with 2 tablespoons flour.
Sprinkle on sugar.
Sprinkle on oleo.
Then sprinkle vanilla over all this.
(Cinnamon or other spices can be added to this pie, if you so choose.)

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken pieces in vegetable oil, then cover with mixture of seasoned bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven 1 1/4 hours.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread mix, cool and crumble.
Fry 5 slices of bacon crisp; crumble.
Dice 1/2 large onion, 1/2 green bell pepper, celery, hard-boiled eggs and tomato.
Mix all this together with real mayonnaise until texture is suitable, as desired.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put in individual crab shells and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in microwave.
Add sugar, vanilla, etc. Mix and put in pan lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Cut in squares.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the eggs, one at a time. Fold in the flour.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine well; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix strawberry jello, water and frozen strawberries.
Set aside and let begin to jell.

title: delicious burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beef, onion, garlic salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into six patties, 3/4-inch thick.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in margarine for 10 minutes, or until shrimp are tender.
Add mushrooms; cook 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream; cook gently for 10 minutes, not allowing mixture to boil.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ashley boone's potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill & serve with crackers.

title: faith-hope cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust by combining the chopped nuts, graham crackers and melted margarine, and press into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Beat together the cottage, cheese, cream cheese, sugar, eggs, cornstarch, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add sour cream and cooled margarine; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Turn oven off and let cake set 10 minutes.

title: bellgogi
directions: Cut steak into very thin slices.
Beat them.
Cut into medium-sized squares.
Make up marinade and let meat soak for 3 hours (longer in the refrigerator).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Put 2 cups of cake mix into a 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Re-coat sides of pan with grease.
Melt caramels, oleo and Pet milk in microwave or double boiler.
Pour caramel mixture over cake and sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over cake.
Then pour rest of cake batter over all and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: hot ham and cheese dip
directions: Hollow out 1 bread.
Mix ingredients.
Place inside bread. Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Use second loaf for dipping.
A guaranteed hit!

title: cheese ball(for little bro - kev)
directions: Add all ingredients.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts of choice.
Freezes well.

title: jello pudding dirt cake
directions: Note:
Need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups and gummy worms and frogs.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add vinegar to milk.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased and lightly floured tube pan
1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs, peeled, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Gradually mix into zucchini mixture.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and chopped dates.
Pour into 2 lightly greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven (makes 3 small or 2 large loaves).

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in casserole.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle on stuffing.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: honey mustard glazed chicken
directions: Saut chicken in olive oil with Mrs. Dash for about 4 minutes.
Stir in mustard and honey; cook 2 minutes.
Add snow peas and peppers.
Cover and cook for about 2 minutes.
Toss gently.
Serve over bed of rice.
Serves 4.

title: frosted pear
directions: Halve pears, remove seeds and place on a dessert plate, cut side up.
Frost each pear half with Creamy Cheese and garnish with a few slivered almonds.
Makes 6 servings, 60 calories per serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add sugars, salt, soda and baking powder to flour and sift twice.
Beat egg.
Add oil, milk, butter and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and apples.
Stir only to moisten.
Add raisins and nuts.

title: egg and potato medley
directions: In frying pan, saute onion in butter.
Add potatoes and fry. Add meat, salt and pepper.
Turn heat to low.
Add slightly beaten eggs to mixture, turning frequently, until eggs are cooked into mixture.
Be careful not to cook too long, or mixture will get dry.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and serve.

title: veal, prosciutto and parmesan rolls
directions: Saute onion in butter until softened.
Add the veal; cook for 3 minutes, or until veal is no longer pink.
Transfer mixture to a bowl with a slotted spoon and add the Prosciutto, Parmesan, pine nuts, currants and spices with salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap in wontons and seal with a wash of one egg and 1 tablespoon water. Deep fry in vegetable oil.
Makes 50.

title: oriental beef
directions: Slightly freeze sirloin steak to make slicing easier.
Trim all fat from beef.
Against the grain of the meat, thinly slice the beef into 1-inch strips.
Size does not have to be exact.
Mix together all ingredients except beef to make marinade.
Place sliced beef into deep bowl and cover with marinade.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.
May be refrigerated up to 8 hours.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 15 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Add all ingredients to browned and drained ground beef.
Stir occasionally until cheese has melted.
Keep warm during serving. Works well on low setting of crock-pot.
Serve with tostada chips.

title: percolator punch
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in bottom of coffeepot.
In the basket, place remaining ingredients.
Perk.
Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Shred cabbage and slice vegetables.
Mix all ingredients into large pot. Simmer slowly for 2 hours, adding water as needed. This is a good diet soup.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice tops off peppers; remove seeds and rinse.
Place peppers in container and cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain peppers and sprinkle cavities with salt.
Mix ground beef, 1 cup crushed potato chips, buttermilk, eggs, catsup and poultry seasoning.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Place filled peppers in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining chips and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and place half in the bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Save the rest of the
crushed
cookies for
the top.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla and set aside.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and
oleo.
Add
pudding
mixture
and blend mixtures.
Cover top with remaining crushed Oreos.

title: raspberry raspberry
directions: In large bowl, pour boiling water over gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin thickens.
Remove any remaining ice cubes.
Add yogurt and beat until smooth.
Pour into individual containers.
Chill and serve. Makes 5 to 6 four ounce servings.

title: rosy pear compote
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and ginger.
Bring to a boil.
Drain all fruits and place pears, peaches and oranges in 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Pour cranberry mixture over fruit.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach melba angel cake
directions: Cut 2-inch top off tube type angel cake.
Hollow out a round angel cake, leaving sides of inch or so.
Put frozen yogurt and fruit topping in tunnel.
Put top back on; firm up in freezer. Cut slices; serve with more fruit topping.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften.
Mix in all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.

title: hand cookies
directions: Heat oven at 425°.
Mix sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla. Blend in remaining ingredients; divide dough in 3 parts.
Roll each part 1/4-inch thick on board.
Trace out hand.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Save a few nuts and cherries to decorate cake.

title: pecan teatime tassies
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine soften.
Blend.
Stir in flour. Chill about 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Place in ungreased small muffin tins.
Flour your fingers and thumb.
Press dough onto bottom and sides, forming a pastry cup.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until a soft ball forms when dropped in water.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer until it starts to get thick.
Pour onto buttered dish.
Let cool and cut.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain off grease.
Fix boiled potatoes into mashed potatoes.
Place potatoes in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Place ground beef mixture on top and spread evenly.
Put cheese on top of meat, enough to cover.
Bake in a 350° oven until browned lightly or melted.
Serve hot.

title: jiffy coconut banana pudding
directions: Prepare your pudding mix according to directions on the box. Arrange the vanilla wafers in a baking dish.
Layer your bananas. Pour the pudding on top of the mixture.
Then repeat the process again.
Keep doing this until you alternate the ingredients and it's used up.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Then spread the meringue over the pudding.
Bake at 425° until the meringue is lightly browned.
Then take out of oven.
Add coconut flakes.
Put back in oven for about 5 minutes.
Take out of oven. Cool for about 10 minutes.
Bon appetit! Scrumptious!

title: good ole days bosom bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Dissolve soda in the buttermilk and place in a loaf pan.
Bake in the oven at 425°.
A small amount of allspice and cloves can be added if desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into well greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until well set.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake the empty pie shell 8 minutes. Allow it to cool.
Reduce oven to 375°.
