In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time until smooth.
Stir in corn syrup, pecans, rum and salt; blend thoroughly.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: "hot shot" fresh tomato relish
directions: Chop all ingredients together.
Place in a bowl and chill. This is delicious with pintos.

title: savory spinach spread
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain well; press out excess liquid.
In a medium saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted and heated through.
Stir in spinach.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: old fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in a skillet until tender. Add mixture to bread cubes which have been placed in a large pan. Sprinkle with seasonings which have been mixed together and mix well. Add water and egg.
Toss together with forks.
Stuff thawed bird and immediately roast.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients and place in baking dish. Top with crumbled crackers. Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered. Serve hot.

title: fabulous quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch glass pie plate.
Combine cheese, poultry, broccoli and onion in prepared pie plate.
Combine milk, pie crust mix, eggs, salt and pepper in a blender.
Mix at high speed until smooth.
Pour over ingredients in pie plate.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken
in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add layer of	grated	onion.	Layer peas.
Spread on soup and then add chicken
broth.
Mix
Bisquick,
butter and milk and cover top of dish
with	this
mixture.	Bake
at
350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's chilli
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; salt and pepper.
Add chili powder.
Stir in flour.
Add tomatoes and water, then beans.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Bring to a boil, then turn to low temperature.

title: 5-minute fondant
directions: Blend Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, mixing until smooth and creamy.
Result:
One and 1/3 pounds real homemade candy.
Can be used between nut meats or stuffing for dates.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Put oleo, cocoa and Coca-Cola in boiler.
Bring to a boil. Combine flour and sugar and pour mixture over.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Add marshmallows.
This is a thin batter and marshmallows will float. Pour into a greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: In a bowl, cut up cheese and butter; melt in microwave.
In a large bowl, mix powdered sugar, cocoa and melted cheese and butter.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan, greased with butter.
Refrigerate until hard (2 or 3 hours). Best if left refrigerated overnight.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, sugar, soda and salt together. Put in measuring cup the juice and grated rind of orange, melted shortening and boiling water, enough to make 3/4 cup of liquid. Add egg and mix with dry ingredients. Do
not beat too much. Add chopped nuts and cranberries. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Keep 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken plavier
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream. Make stuffing. Place cooked chicken in casserole. Cover with soup mixture and top with stuffing. Bake at 350 for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: peppermint schnapps
directions: Bring water and sugar to a hard boil.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add 1 pint Everclear and peppermint extract.
Bottle and enjoy.

title: wisconsin beef pot roast
directions: Trim separable fat from roast.
Rub 1 side with lemon-pepper seasoning.
In a Dutch oven brown roast on all sides in hot oil. Drain off fat.
Combine the 1/2 cup water, tomato juice, beef broth or water, bouillon granules and thyme.
Pour around roast in Dutch oven.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour (or bake in a 325° oven, covered, for 1 hour).
Add carrots, potatoes and onions to meat.
Cover; simmer or bake 45 to 60 minutes more or until tender, adding additional water, if necessary.
Use a slotted spoon to remove meat and vegetables; keep warm.

title: coconut truffles
directions: Melt chocolate over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool. Cream butter with yolk.
Gradually add sugar, blending well. Stir in chocolate and liqueur.
Chill until firm enough to handle. Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in coconut; chill.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes about 30.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: In skillet, lightly brown ground beef; drain well.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper; set aside.
Place half the potatoes and half the onions in greased crock-pot.
Add browned beef.
Top with remaining potatoes and onions.
Combine mushroom soup and water; spread over top, being sure to moisten and cover evenly.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pumpkin pie and more
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 12 pan.
Blend next 3 ingredients and spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Beat egg yolks and add pumpkin, sugar, milk, salt and cinnamon. Cook 5 minutes until thick.
Soften gelatin in water and add water to pumpkin mixture.
Let cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar; fold into the cool pumpkin mixture.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Allow to set in refrigerator until firm.
Then top with Cool Whip and cover.

title: mini cinnamon nut puffs
directions: Thaw pastry sheets.
Cut along folds to make three pieces. Roll each piece out to about twice its size.
Spread with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and nuts which have been mixed together.
Roll each piece over twice lengthwise and press edges together.
Brush with egg wash (to make wash mix egg and water together) and cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1/2-inch apart and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned and puffed nicely.
Glaze with a mixture of butter, powdered sugar, milk and vanilla, if desired. Yields approximately 60 goodies.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Stir in ice cream until smooth.
Pour into glass serving bowl.
Add fruit once chilled and set.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip and nuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and seasonings and bring to boil.
Add noodles and stir.
Simmer and cook 30 minutes or until noodles are done.
Pour into casserole and top with grated cheese.
Place under broiler or bake until cheese is melted.
If made ahead of time and refrigerated, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips, press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and garnish as desired.
Cut into bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: dutch bean stew(germany)
directions: Bring to boil 2 cups salted water.
Prepare the string beans, cut in half inch lengths.
Boil them, uncovered, in the water, adding the butter.
Peel and dice the potatoes, and add them to the beans after the beans have boiled 15 minutes.
Boil for 15 more minutes; then sift in the flour, sprinkle with pepper and add the vinegar.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown ground beef. Layer in buttered baking dish the sliced potatoes, sliced onions, celery, ground beef, peppers and kidney beans. Top with tomato soup. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: french onion beef au jus
directions: Combine in slow cooker and cook 10 hours (or in Dutch oven in 325° oven for 3 hours).
Let set for 20 minutes, then thinly slice.
Make sandwiches on buttered French or hard rolls.
Top with Swiss cheese, if desired.
Serve with bowls of broth for dipping.

title: vegetable and sausage skillet
directions: Put 2 tablespoons oil in electric skillet.
Cut cabbage into 8 parts and place on bottom of skillet.
Cut carrots and potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Place on top of cabbage.
Add onion, cut in large pieces, then put sausage which has been cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces on top.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of water over these.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook with lid on skillet over medium heat for approximately 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in heated juice from cherries and pineapple, then add Cokes, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Grate frozen cream cheese over top of mold (gives appearance of snow).
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Frozen Cokes make it congeal faster. Delicious and perfect for Thanksgiving and Christmas.
Serves 10.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups candies; reserve remaining for decoration.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combine flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chopped candies and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately press 3 reserved candies into top of each cookie.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: quick corned beef and cabbage(microwave)
directions: Grease a 3-quart casserole; layer potatoes and onions.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook on High for 8 or 9 minutes. Crumble corned beef on top; cut cabbage into 4 wedges.
Place on top of corned beef.
Pour butter over cabbage.
Cover.
Cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes (until cabbage is tender).
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook water, syrup and sugar until it spins a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff with salt.
Add cooked syrup slowly while beating.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens.
Add pecans and beat by hand until mixture loses its glossy look.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 10 cups salad.

title: mickie's sweet and sour pork
directions: Put in a bowl, 4 tablespoons cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sherry or pineapple juice and 4 tablespoons soy sauce.
Toss pork in this mixture.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add 3 cups flour or more to make dough stiff, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Nuts may be added.

title: french garlic chicken
directions: Press 4 garlic cloves in small dish with lemon juice.
Rub mixture over chicken.
Marinate 10 minutes.
Melt butter and oil in large skillet.
Add chicken; saute until browned.
Add mushrooms, wine, bay leaf and remaining garlic.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Blend mustard and broth and add to skillet.
Cook, covered, another 15 minutes.
Remove chicken and whole garlic. Discard bay leaf.
Bring pan liquids to a boil and cook until reduced and thickened.
Pour over chicken.
Spread garlic cloves on crusty French baguette.

title: tropical ice
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in 2 refrigerator trays or metal cake pan.
Freeze almost solid.
Stir with a spoon to make smooth (or mix with mixer).
Freeze several hours.
Can be used as dessert or drinks.
Add 7-Up over top for a great punch.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and reserve juice.
Add eggs and enough milk to make 1 cup.
Combine this with all other ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In one bowl, mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
In a different bowl, mix flour, salt and nuts together with your hands.
Mix flour mixture with sugar mixture.
Make a dough into 1-inch balls.
Place them on a greased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until set or not doughy anymore. While warm, roll the balls in confectioners sugar.
Let the balls cool.
Roll in sugar again.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
(Yes, the icing goes into the batter.) Spray a Bundt pan with cooking spray.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool cake in pan about 10 to 15 minutes.
Then enjoy.

title: chunky chicken-cheese bake
directions: Place chicken in a 3-quart dish.
Cook in oven until almost done at 350°.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese. Top with tomato slices.
Combine oleo and stuffing mix; sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, until chicken is tender.

title: scripture cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 4-inch angel cake tube pan.
Preheat oven slow to 325°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice onto wax paper.
Beat the butter, sugar, honey and eggs in a large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour mixture over fruits and nuts.
Add remaining flour mixture alternately with milk to the fluffy butter mixture, beating until smooth. Stir in fruits and nuts.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated slow oven at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched with fingertip.
Cool on wire rack in pan for 20 minutes.
Loosen around edges with knife. Turn out on rack.
Cool completely.
Wrap in foil or plastic. Cake slices best the next day.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until they form a peak.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in flavoring and nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: won't last cake(banana nut)
directions: Freeze applesauce in popsicle trays for a delicious and refreshing low-sugar summer treat.
Your children will love it!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar. Add eggs, hot water and vanilla.
Beat well and add sifted together:
cake flour, salt and soda.
Add chocolate and pecans. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet, spacing 2 inches apart.
Bake in slow 300° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: five fruit salad
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add orange.
Top with cover; process about 10 seconds.
Scrape sides of bowl with a rubber spatula and process orange an additional 3 to 5 seconds, or until finely chopped.
Combine orange and the next 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Garnish with grated orange rind, if desired.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, milk and cream.
Add dry ingredients to liquid.
Add melted butter and mix well.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, and Crisco well.
Add eggs one at a time, yolks only.
Mix well.
Sift flour and soda together; add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add coconut and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes in three layer pans.

title: squash cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Poach chicken for 15 minutes in a big pot.
Skin, bone and shred.
Combine next 6 ingredients for the dressing.
Pour 1/2 over chicken.
Reserve the rest.
Make pasta.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Put peaches in blender or mash until fine.
Add sugar.
Mix milk, condensed milk and sour cream together.
Add peaches and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pork chops on top of potatoes
directions: In oblong Pyrex dish, approximately 9 x 12-inches, slice in small pieces, enough potatoes to layer the bottom of dish or enough to feed 4 people.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in enough milk to keep potatoes from sticking (about 1/2 cup).
Dice Velveeta cheese (about 1/2 pound) on top of potatoes..
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are good and brown.
Onions can be sliced in potatoes, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Knead ingredients together and mold into a ball.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove from oven and top with crescent rolls, cheese and French fried onions.
Bake another 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Stir uncooked rice into cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups.
Layer broccoli, rice-soup mixture and cheese in a baking dish.
Repeat layering process. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Makes a 13 x 9-inch size dish.

title: tuna fiesta soft tacos
directions: In large bowl, combine mayo, garlic salt, lemon pepper, tuna, celery, egg, onion, bell pepper and pimiento.
Mix thoroughly. Place generous 1/2 cup filling on one side of each tortilla.
Top with lettuce and cheese.
Fold tortillas over; serve with salsa, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In skillet, brown and drain the beef, onion and green pepper. Add tomatoes (chop slightly in blender), mushrooms, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti noodles and drain.
Place half of the noodles in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Top with half the ground beef mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Cheddar. Repeat layers.
Mix can of cream of mushroom soup with 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Pour over casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes (do not overcook).
Peel and slice in serving dish.
Fry bacon, break or crumble, and set aside.
Mix sugar, flour and mustard and stir into bacon drippings.
Gradually add vinegar.
Cook until thickens.
Add chopped celery, onion, radishes and parsley to potatoes.
Add broken up pieces of bacon. Pour vinegar gravy over all.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Add one egg at a time. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk. Add flavoring. Put in a cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: enchiladas acapulco
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup green pepper over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and 1/4 pound cheese; continue to cook until cheese is melted.
Dip tortilla in hot oil; drain and fill each tortilla with 1/4 cup of mixture and roll up.
Place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining meat mixture; cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with remaining pepper and tomatoes.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Add macaroni.
Boil eggs.
Place tuna, relish, chopped onion and Miracle Whip in bowl.
Stir; add to macaroni.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in heated (bubbling) cherry pie filling. Remove from heat.
Stir in crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Add chopped nuts and 7-Up.
Mix and pour into large dish or bowl.
Let jell.
This is pretty for Christmas.

title: stir-fried chicken with linguine
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil until just done.
Add all ingredients and stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Combine cornstarch, ginger and soy sauce.
Add to stock and mix well.
Add to vegetables and chicken.
Cook 2 minutes, until thickened.
Serve over cooked linguine or with cooked rice.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with grated Cheddar cheese, Thousand Island or French dressing and hot sauce to taste. Crunch and add Doritos tortilla chips.
Slice and add avocado. Brown ground beef; add kidney beans and salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes; mix into cold salad.
Decorate with tortilla chips, avocado and tomato slices.

title: traditional no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: In a small bowl, blend milk, egg, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
In medium saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over water.
Let it stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Blend in milk mixture.
Continue stirring over low heat until mixture is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Blend in pumpkin.
Turn into prepared crust; chill until firm.
Garnish, if desired, with whipped cream. Serves 8.

title: fiesta punch
directions: Mix
sugar
with
cups of the water.
Bring to boil; cool. Combine
this
syrup
with
the remaining 2 cups water, lemon juice,
cranberry
juice, pineapple juice and the salt. Freeze. When
ready
to
use,
put in punch bowl and pour Dr. Pepper over it.
Break up into a slush or instead of freezing, keep concentrate
in
refrigerator until time to serve.
When ready
to serve,
pour
over
ice
and add Dr. Pepper.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 quarts or 25 to 30 servings.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt caramels, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and brown sugar, stirring
constantly.
Set	aside.	Mix
cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated
milk and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spread half of the batter
in	a
greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for
6 minutes
(batter
should
still
be
very soft).
Pour caramel mixture evenly over crust and sprinkle chocolate chips over
the top.
Crumble remaining brownie mixture on the top. Bake for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together cranberries, oranges and celery.
Add sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 3/4 cups hot water.
Add with other ingredients in oblong baking dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, but add 7-Up last.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spicy apple muffins
directions: Sprinkle apples with 1/4 cup sugar. Set aside. Blend together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream together the powdered sugar and butter.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Mix well until light and fluffy.
Spread this in the 2 pie crusts.
Chill.
Whip the cream until stiff; blend in the pineapple (drained) and nuts.
Spoon on top of the sugar, butter mixture and chill again.

title: 7 layer bar
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add in layers: graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let the cheese warm to room temperature; add the bottle of shrimp cocktail and steak sauce.
Stir by hand until uniform.
A blender will shred the shrimp.

title: apple pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. Mix water, vinegar and egg thoroughly, then add to dry mixture. Makes double crust pie.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Grind rolled oats in blender until fine.
Add all ingredients into bread maker pan, yeast first, then flour.
Then add remaining ingredients, saving the water until last.
Select "white bread" setting.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift flour with soda.
Beat eggs and sugar; add oil, then flour and soda.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.
Makes 3 layers.
Grease and flour pans.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Mix all the preceding.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Make white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and salt.
Add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Arrange broccoli and pasta in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (1/2 cup).
Cover with chicken (diced or shredded).
Top with sauce and remaining cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(Let stand 10 minutes before serving.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapples and mix all ingredients together.

title: curry surprise appetizers
directions: Combine the chicken with the chopped apple, green onion, peanuts, the mayonnaise, curry powder and hot sauce in a large bowl, blending well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours or until well chilled.
Shape the chilled chicken mixture into 1-inch balls (about 1 tablespoon each).
Roll in the shredded coconut on wax paper.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 24.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine gelatin
and
boiling water; stir until gelatin dissolves.	Add
next
4 ingredients.
Divide mixture in half; freeze half juice mixture and chill remaining half.
To serve, partially thaw frozen
mixture,
then
place in punch bowl and break into chunks.	Stir
in
chilled juice mixture and ginger ale.
Yields 7 quarts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, milk and flour.
Pour into Dutch oven with melted butter.
Pour peaches over mixtures; sprinkle cinnamon over peaches.
Cover Dutch oven with lid.
Place hot coals over top and under.

title: berry cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Cream all until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pans in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir together thoroughly and put in two unbaked pie shells. Bake 70 minutes at 375°.

title: grandma's vegetarian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and let it stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon in hot vegetable oil and slowly brown on both sides. Make sure cream cheese is softened.
Cover with mushroom soup. Dilute with milk (optional).

title: potato, ham and green bean soup(my favorite)
directions: Cut potatoes up into about 1-inch pieces.
Add water until it covers the potatoes.
Boil in a large pot about 1/2 hour (until pieces break easily).
Add butter and ham; cook 15 minutes.
Add green beans.
Add a little water if needed to make consistency. Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Put frozen strawberries in hot jello and stir until melted; add crushed pineapple and stir well.
Pour into shallow dish and chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: baked ranch chicken
directions: Combine Ranch dip mix, bread crumbs and cheese and toss. Dip chicken breasts in milk and then into bread crumb mixture. Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish that has been coated with nonstick spray and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cut celery into pieces and cook in 1/2 cup water for 8 minutes. Drain and reserve water. Mix celery, soup and reserved water and put in casserole. Melt butter. Add crumbs to melted butter until absorbed, no more. Spread crumbs over casserole and bake at 3509° for 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix vinegar and baking soda and let settle.
Set aside. Combine
remaining
ingredients
then add vinegar, baking soda mixture.
Bake in
(9-inch)
pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar and soda.
Mix in eggs and fruit cocktail and mix 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top the brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot water.
Cool slightly.
Add the rest of the ingredients and pour into a mold.
Refrigerate.
Goes well with ham.

title: shrimp ring
directions: Warm the cream cheese with the tomato soup.
Add the Knox gelatine mixed with warm water. Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Pour into mold and let set overnight.

title: green bean and mozzarella salad
directions: Cook and drain green beans.
Cut Mozzarella into 1/2-inch cubes.
Slice plum tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: linguine with spinach, carrots and leeks
directions: *A mixture of tri-color pastas is nice with this recipe.

title: oats and raisins cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; mix well.
Drop heaping teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Heat the milk and chocolate together over low heat, stirring constantly.
Beat until smooth and add the salt, sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.

title: chicken in oriental dipping sauce
directions: Put all ingredients except chicken in
a medium size microwave-safe bowl.
Mix and cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for three minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring once during cooking.
Serve with cooked chicken.

title: easy crab soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Heat on medium until boiling.
Serve topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Partly thaw broccoli before mixing.
Beat egg and soup together.
Mix all together, except half of cheese.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: overnight coffeecake
directions: Cream
sugars
with
margarine	and
add eggs. Sift dry ingredients
together
and	add
to the mixture.
Add the sour cream and mix by hand.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with a mixture of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: toffee nut bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Put in a 9x13 cake pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees. Cut while hot.

title: baked pineapple with brown sugar
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange pineapple in single layer on baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Drizzle with Kahlua.
Bake until juices bubble, about 25 minutes.
Transfer any juices to small saucepan and boil until thickened to sauce consistency.
Arrange pineapple on plates.
Top with ice cream.
Spoon sauce over and serve hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Mix together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture, then add zucchini.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: shrimp diane on pasta(makes 2 servings)
directions: Rinse
and
peel the shrimp;
refrigerate until needed. In a large
skillet
melt 1 stick of the butter.
When almost melted, add
the
green onions, salt, garlic, the ground peppers, basil, thyme and oregano; stir well.
Add the shrimp and saute just until
they
turn pink, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add the mushrooms and
1/4 cup of the chicken stock, then add the remaining 4 tablespoons butter in chunks and continue cooking. Before
the butter
chunks
are
completely
melted,
add the parsley,
then the
remaining
2 tablespoons stock.
Continue cooking
and shaking
the pan until all ingredients are mixed thoroughly
and butter
sauce
is
the
consistency of cream. Serve over
a
bowl of pasta or rice with French bread on the side.

title: crescent chicken bundles
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion, cheese and pimento.
Stir. Separate rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture into center and pull four corners of dough to center and seal.
Brush tops with butter and sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Roll out pie crust and put in 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, eggs, nuts and vanilla.
Pour on baked crust and bake pizza 10 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Add cherry pie filling.
Chill.
Just before serving, add dairy whipped topping. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: georgia chewy pecan pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and heavy cream in heavy 10-inch skillet.
Bring to boiling over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Once it boils, stop stirring and boil 4 minutes. Mixture should be thick with large bubbles on surface.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir some of hot mixture into egg.
Stir back into skillet.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: aunt dey's potato salad
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Fold in mayonnaise and add salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party mix
directions: Break pretzel sticks into smaller pieces.
Add nuts and cereals.
Melt
butter.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion and celery
salts.
Mix; cover and bake 1 hour in a 225° oven.
Remove
cover
and
bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 quarts.

title: cocoa puffs candy
directions: Bring the Karo syrup and sugar to a boil; stir 20 times.
Mix all together.
Press into buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions and chipped beef.
Combine all ingredients and form into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift, then measure again with baking powder and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Mix only enough to moisten flour.
Drop by tablespoon on gently bubbling stew.
Cook 10 minutes with kettle uncovered and 10 minutes with kettle covered.
Serve at once. Don't crowd in kettle, allow room for expansion.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all and place in 7 x 11-inch glass dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 300°
about 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: glazed graham crackers
directions: Soften butter and mix with sugar, vanilla and nuts; spread over graham crackers and put on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Cook ground beef and pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Stir in chili mix, tomato paste, cream cheese and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm.

title: brad's hot punch(must be made in percolator)
directions: Place brown sugar, cinnamon sticks and dash of allspice in coffee ground section of percolator.

title: nancy's throwaway soup
directions: Place chicken, celery, carrots, whole onion, bay leaf, oregano, salt, pepper and water in large kettle.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer, partially covered, for 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to platter. Boil broth over high heat until reduced to 2 quarts.
Strain broth; return to kettle.
Throw away vegetables.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, green pepper and chopped onion.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add corn and okra.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender.
Remove and discard skin and bones from chicken.
Cut meat into small cubes; add to kettle.
Bring soup gently to boiling.
Spoon into warmed soup bowls.

title: hot german potato soup
directions: Saute potatoes, onions, celery and carrots in olive oil.
When lightly browned, add other ingredients, except milk and instant potatoes.
Cook 30 minutes, covered, on low heat.
Turn off heat and add milk and instant potatoes.
Stir.
If too thick, add a cup of water.
Serve with a dab of sour cream on top, crusty rye bread and spinach salad.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook in separate saucepans until tender.
Drain well.
Put cauliflower in bottom of greased casserole.
Spread broccoli on top of cauliflower.
Heat mayonnaise, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and lemon juice until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: dad's baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, salt and sugar into mixing bowl.
Add the shortening to
the flour mixture and mix thoroughly until cornmeal like consistency.
Add milk to this mixture slow like (a little at a time).
Add the eggs and stir to a stiff dough.
Pour out on floured countertop and knead just enough to make a soft dough when rolled out to approximately 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 3-inch cutter.
Bake in 450° preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 24 biscuits.

title: crab treat
directions: Soften butter with cheese spread, garlic salt, mayonnaise and seasoned salt.
Pick any shells out of crabmeat; drain and add crabmeat to cheese.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze 10 minutes; cut into eighths or quarters.
Broil on cookie sheet or in toaster oven until bubbly.
May be kept frozen until ready to broil. Makes 96 (1/8 size) wedges or 48 (1/4 size) wedges.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind up the fresh cranberries, orange rind and the apples. Add the other ingredients, adding the dissolved jello last.
Mix well and cool in refrigerator.
This keeps for a long time.

title: alzina's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add molasses and egg and blend.
Sift dry ingredients except oats.
Drop on cookie sheet and flatten with wet fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mix.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in apples, pecans and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cornstarch; add milk alternately.
Add margarine and stir until smooth.
Cook in heavy saucepan over medium heat until slightly thick.
Add vanilla. Alternately place sliced bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding mixture (don't make it too dry) in a baking dish.
Beat egg whites and add 4 teaspoons sugar.
Beat again; spread over pudding and bake in a preheated oven until meringue is slightly brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add bananas, milk, oil and vinegar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Stir with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (standard bread pan; 1/2 hour for small bread pans or test off center with toothpick).
Use greased and floured pan.

title: shooger cookies
directions: First you mix up the shooger and the dough.
When that's finished, take the dough and make it into balls.
Put them in the oven at 500° for about an hour and a half.
Then eat them.

title: plantation soda crackers*
directions: *An 1855 recipe.
Good for gumming, ...teething babies or toothless old men.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium heat. Cook onion, if desired, in butter 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened. Remove from heat. Add 1
cups cheese and stir until cheese is melted. Combine cheese sauce with cooked macaroni. Pour into 1
quart casserole; top with remaining cheese. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is lightly browned.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine fruit and flour.
Pour milk and vanilla over this. Mix well. Put on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk-coconut pie
directions: Beat
eggs
well.
Add
all other ingredients, one at a time, beating
well after each.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook 3 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making 2 layers.
When cool, split layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Spread between layers and stack cake.
Spread on top.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Blend flour, soda and salt; mix with other ingredients.
Add pecans, coconut and cornflakes (Carol uses honey and nut cornflakes).
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes. Don't grease cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine crumbs, butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Work together until smooth.
Press this mixture into a 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together. Best made a day in advance. Add more sour cream if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook popcorn in hot air popper.
Heat other ingredients on medium heat until bubbly.
Drizzle over popcorn and stir to coat. Spread
out
on
cookie
sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 12 hours. Mash potatoes before serving.
Top with chives for added flavor and color.

title: crab salad(ultra low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium-sized bowl.
Chill before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
Less than 1 gram of fat per serving and 79 calories per serving.
Looks pretty served on a lettuce leaf or use as a stuffing for tomatoes.
Also good as a spread on crackers or a sandwich.

title: five-hour stew(serves 8)
directions: The evening before dredge stew meat in flour and brown in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake, covered, for 5 hours at 250°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake a yellow cake.
Let cool, then slice lengthwise in middle and put filling between layers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients except butter.
Mix well and form into 48 small balls.
Brown in butter; then add water to simmer, about 1 1/2 cups.
Cook covered 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles. These freeze well and can be made smaller to use as an appetizer.

title: molded applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce and add gelatin.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients and pour into 1 large mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves and serve with mayonnaise.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl, blend ingredients with a wire whisk, just enough to moisten.
Dip up batter with a large serving spoon. Bake on a preheated nonstick griddle.
Turn pancakes when top side is bubbly and a few bubbles have broken.
Flip only once.
Makes 20 pancakes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage and sirloin in a skillet until browned; drain well.
Set aside.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven.
Add flour and cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture turns color of a copper penny (about 8 minutes).
Stir in onion, celery, 1/2 of green onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in meat and remaining green onions; cook until thoroughly heated.
Cook rice.
Add rice and mix well.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese until well blended.
Fill each shell with a heaping tablespoon of spinach mixture.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish; spoon sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Combine beans and water in a large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 4 hours or until beans reach desired tenderness.
Add additional water if needed.

title: ham and egg salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
In large bowl, combine macaroni, ham, peas, chopped eggs and onion.
Blend in separate bowl the mayonnaise, mustard, salt and sugar.
Toss dressing with salad, then add cheese and mix well.
Chill.

title: chip and pretzel dip
directions: Beat with hand mixer.

title: gingerbread
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy pan and let cool.
Add the sugar and egg and beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Combine the molasses, honey, hot water and grated orange rind.
Add the sifted and liquid ingredients alternately to the butter mixture until blended.
Bake in a greased pan about 1 hour.

title: aunt jo's buttermilk pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Stir just enough to blend eggs and sugar mixture.
Do not beat.
Add milk and vanilla and again stir just enough to blend.
Add melted butter.
Pour int pie shells.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour or until the center is firm when you shake it.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Combine applesauce, sugar and vinegar.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 5 hours.
Reduce heat to low and cook another 3 hours. Add cinnamon oil.
Pour into sterilized pint jars and seal.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in dish and top with grated cheese and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix together egg yolks, flour, sugar and butter.
Pour mixture over rhubarb.
Beat egg whites and mix in with rhubarb mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease 2 layer pans.
Line bottom with wax paper.
Sift together ingredients into large bowl.
Stir in water and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool, then remove from pans. Frost as desired.

title: applesauce cake a la mode
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and spices into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and applesauce; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes more.
Blend in fruits and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in order given with electric mixer, beating constantly at medium speed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves; freezes well.

title: horseradish beets
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and horseradish.
Add to
beets. Refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli.
Add to the cooked rice.
Saute the onion in margarine.
Add the soup.
Place one layer of broccoli and rice in casserole.
Place 4 slices of cheese on this.
Repeat this and pour the soup mix over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Heat Cheez Whiz in microwave until runny.
Melt margarine slightly in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together.
Toast muffins and spread mixture on.
Cut each muffin half in quarters and put on cookie sheets.
Freeze on sheets in freezer 30 minutes. Put in plastic bag and keep frozen until needed.
Take out, as needed, and warm on cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and sugar.	Gradually add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in flour. Add vanilla.	Bake in tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: brandied strawberries
directions: Thaw and drain strawberries.
In large saucepan combine sugar and water.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Stir in strawberries and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in brandy.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Use any kind of fruit you like:
bananas, orange slices, apple slices, grapes, pineapple chunks or anything you have to use.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together thoroughly.
Add melted margarine and mix; mixture will be crumbly.
This is the topping. Spread apples in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix lemon juice and water. Pour over apples.
Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese to garnish top.
It is best to mix with your hands.
Add milk to thin, if needed.
Butter casserole dish, bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Oil a jelly roll pan or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine sugar, salt, milk or cream and corn syrup in a heavy 3-quart pot, stirring to mix well.
Stir over medium until boils, then cover and let boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Uncover and wash down the sides of the pot with a pastry brush dipped in cold water.
Continue to boil over medium heat, without stirring, to the soft ball stage (234°).
Put the pot on a cooking surface or rack, without stirring.
Let the syrup cool to a lukewarm (110°).
Mix in the peanut butter and vanilla, stirring until thickened.
Spread in the oiled pan.
Cut into squares when formed and store airtight.

title: lit'l smokies
directions: Mix jelly and mustard in heated crock pot until well blended. Add smokies.
Serve when heated through.

title: chocolate eclair "cake"
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Repeat layer of graham crackers and remaining pudding mixture.
Top pudding with third layer of whole graham crackers.
Set can of chocolate frosting in hot water for a few minutes to make it easier to spread.
Spread frosting over top layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: gorilla knuckles
directions: Melt margarine and cheese; make a sauce.
Blend in flour, garlic, olives and paprika.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato pancakes *
directions: In the food processor, process half the potatoes with the steel blade knife.
Process the onions with the steel blade knife. Process the rest of the potatoes with the shredder blade.
Put processed potatoes and onions in colander.
Pour boiling water over and drain.
Put in bowl.
Add eggs, matzo meal, salt and pepper and mix well.
Fry in hot oil, using a heaping tablespoonful of batter for each pancake.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Can be frozen.
Freeze in single layer on cookie sheets. When frozen, put in plastic bag.

title: shrimp fiesta
directions: Saute onion in butter and stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat through and serve over rice.

title: baked potato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
This mixture will keep indefinitely under refrigeration.
A great alternative to sour cream.

title: paradise pie
directions: In a large bowl, blend cream cheese by hand.
With a spoon, blend with remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.

title: bounce
directions: Add sugar to fruit.
Fill to top of fruit filled jar with vodka and shake to dissolve sugar.
Put lid on tight.
Set 3 to 4 months. Drain fruit and store liquid in pretty container.
Serve and enjoy.

title: speedy skillet steaks
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Dredge steaks in flour mixture.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Add steaks and cook over medium heat 5 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels and wipe skillet clean.
Return steaks to skillet.
Add wine, water and onion.
Cover and simmer 6 minutes or until steaks are tender.
Add tomato wedges to skillet.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes or until completely heated.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Put 1/4 cup bacon grease in pan and heat in oven.
Pour ingredients in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together (do not use blender).
Use large wooden spoon.
Add flour (I use self-rising flour and baking powder).
Mash the peaches after draining them, use a potato masher.
Do not use blender.
The peaches are the liquid. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 2-quart ungreased glass baking dish. Spread chili over cream cheese. Cover with shredded cheese. Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until shredded cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix together next 3 ingredients and spread over crust.

title: four cheese vegetable lasagna
directions: Press spinach between paper towels until barely moist and set aside.
Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add oil and place over medium heat until hot.
Add broccoli and next 4 ingredients; saute for 7 minutes and set aside.
Place flour in a medium saucepan.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; cook another minute.
Remove from heat; stir in spinach.
Reserve 1/2 cup and set aside.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Add 2 cups water, rice and tomatoes.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Add vegetables, noodles and enough water, as desired, for soup. Check for seasoning and add 1 bouillon cube, if needed.
Simmer about 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Serve rather thick.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: sichuan beef and snow peas
directions: Slice beef across grain into thin strips.
Combine 1 tablespoon each cornstarch and soy sauce with sherry and garlic in small bowl; stir in beef.
Let sit 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine water, remaining 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and red pepper; set aside.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring water and rice to boil; add salt. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add milk; stir occasionally, until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla; gradually stir into rice mixture and mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
If desired, stir in raisins and sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon over top.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain juice from salmon into measuring cup.
Mix salmon and egg and add flour.
Add 1/4 cup juice to baking powder.
Pour into salmon mixture.
Drop by teaspoons into deep fat.
Turn until brown.

title: kraut relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill 12 hours before serving.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients together until blended well.
Refrigerate.

title: all-american burgers
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine egg and sour cream dip.
Stir in bread crumbs, Heinz 57 sauce and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into four 3/4-inch thick patties.
Place patties on an unheated rack in a broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from the heat to desired doneness, turning once (allow about 9 minutes total for medium).
Or grill patties on an uncovered grill, directly over medium-hot coals to desired doneness, turning once (allow 6 to 8 minutes total for medium).
Top burgers with cheese slices.
Heat just until cheese melts.
Serve each burger on a lettuce-lined bun with a tomato slice and onion slice and 2 bacon slices.
Serve.
Pass ketchup. Makes 4 servings.

title: poached chicken
directions: In
medium size saucepan or Dutch oven heat chicken and water to a boil; skim off foam.
Add salt, onion and parsley. Reduce heat;
cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender when
pierced.
Cool
in
broth.
Lift
out
chicken. Discard skin;
remove meat from bones in large pieces.
Strain broth and save for soups
or	sauces.
Makes	about 1 pound or 2 1/2 cups cubes or strips of cooked chicken.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl.
Pour into oiled casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, toss noodles with Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Add the browned ground beef to the spaghetti sauce.

title: dove in brown gravy
directions: Put butter, parsley, thyme, clove, ginger and pepper in bottom of pan.
Add doves, then add vinegar and onion.
Half cover with water and add salt.
Cover and cook until tender.
Remove doves from pan and set in warm place.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix together oil, garlic and onions; add other ingredients. Heat and simmer 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: mushroom stew
directions: Cube meat and brown in oil (olive oil preferred).
Chop onions and celery; add to meat.
Mince garlic; add to meat mixture, then add the tomatoes and a little water.
Simmer about 3 hours, then add peppers and mushrooms.
Simmer 2 more hours.
Enjoy with hot bread.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Blend all ingredients, except tortillas, until smooth.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Roll tortillas in damp paper towels and refrigerate in Ziploc bags. Cut into bite-size pieces and serve with picante sauce.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add brown sugar gradually, then the beaten eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Let stand in refrigerator until well chilled.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sour cream and bake in a 300° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: danish glogg
directions: Pour liquids in crock-pot.
Add sugar, spices and flavorings. Heat almost to boiling and serve.

title: spaghetti-pizza deluxe
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and rinse well. In medium bowl, blend milk and egg. Add spaghetti and toss together. Spray 10 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. Spread spaghetti mixture in prepared pan.

title: 100% parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray baking pan with nonstick spray.
Dip chicken in butter, then in the remaining ingredients mixed together.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: aunt lil's low cholesterol crepes
directions: Mix flour and salt, add milk.
Slowly add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Let set for 1/2 hour.
Batter should resemble thin pan cake batter, if not, add a little more milk.
Using a heavy small fry pan (nonstick) or a crepe maker (grease for first crepe), drop 2 tablespoons mixture onto surface, spread even.
Cook for 1 minute and transfer to cooling rack.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place ground beef in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer cabbage and onions over beef.
Cover with tomato soup.
Cook, covered, in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut orange slices into small pieces.
Chop dates and chop pecans.
Mix with coconut, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Mix all together.
Beat eggs and pour over mixture (will be stiff). Put by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken-corn chowder
directions: Cook and debone chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
In large pan, cook potatoes, carrots and onion in chicken broth.
Add additional water if needed to cover vegetables.
When vegetables are tender, add seasoning, chicken, corn and chicken soup.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes until heated.
Serve with cornbread muffins.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach of excess moisture.
Finely chop and set aside.
In large bowl, combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in soup mix, mixing well.
Fold in spinach, other chopped vegetables and seasonings, blending until well combined.
Cover and chill overnight.
Garnish with radish slices.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 6 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken tostados
directions: Place tortillas on a Teflon baking sheet.
Heat in a 350° oven for 3 minutes; turn and heat 3 more minutes or until warm.
Spread tortillas with chicken.
Top with lettuce, tomato, onion, green chilies, cheese, salsa and yogurt or sour cream (fat-free).

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Whip the cream cheese until fluffy. Add milk.
Cream until fluffy. Add lemon juice.
Cream.
Add vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill overnight or at least 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish. Top with strip of bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream together butter and 1 cup sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish, 9 x 9-inch.
Combine cherries with remaining sugar and 1/4 cup juice and heat.
Pour cherries over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Delicious topped with cream or ice cream.
When baked, cherries will be at the bottom and cake on top.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt and stir into first four ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.
Will puff up at first, then flatten out.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Stir in soup (undiluted).
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat and stir in parsley and cooked noodles.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Mix flour and butter with pastry cutter. Add nuts. Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes. "Cool."

title: inside-outside ravioli casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in the 1 tablespoon of oil.
Cook spinach according to directions on package; drain, reserving the liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Stir spinach liquid and next 5 ingredients into meat mixture; simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Top with meat sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mamie eisenhower fudge
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until melted. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Store in tin box.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix shortening, granulated sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix in flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla, then add rolled oats and chocolate chips.
Stir well and drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Cook and drain hamburger meat.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz into meat.
Put into crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve with chips.

title: impossible pie
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients except nutmeg.
Pour into a 10 inch pie plate, sprinkle with nutmeg, and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
When it is done, you will have a crust on the bottom with a custard like pie.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly;
cool.
Beat
in sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at
a
time;
beat until well mixed.
Add flour, salt and nuts;
mix	well.
Turn
into a greased 8-inch square pan.	Bake at	350°
for
minutes.
When
cool, frost with Butter Frosting
or
sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar. Cut into squares.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut stem ends from pepper and remove seeds.
Put peppers in boiling water and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from water and drain.
Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Add ground beef, onion, chopped pepper, corn, salt and black pepper with mixture.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peachy fruit salad
directions: To keep fruit from turning brown, stir into the peach pie filling as you are coring and dicing or peeling and slicing. Place the pie filling into a large bowl.
Add fresh fruit.
Add the pineapple and marshmallows last.
Cover and store in the refrigerator until serving.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: This is a Southern bread that is very delicious and usually eaten with fresh pork, turnip greens, etc.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Let butter, peanut butter, eggs and buttermilk warm to room temperature for easy mixing (butter should be very soft).

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Chill 1 hour.

title: mystical chocolate cheesecake(makes 12 servings)
directions: Finely roll 25 cookies; coarsely chop remaining 10 cookies and set aside.
In medium bowl, mix finely rolled crumbs and margarine.
Press on bottom and 1 inch up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Remove skin from chicken pieces.
Place in large casserole dish in a single layer.
Season, cover with cream of chicken soup. Cover then with Cheddar cheese.
Spread sour cream over cheese layer. Top with crushed croutons. Bake 1 1/4 hour at 350°.

title: italian bowknots(easter cookies)
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Beat in salt, sugar, oil and vanilla. Mix in flour and baking powder. Dough will be sticky.
Roll dough into ropes with hands, using about 1 tablespoon dough.
Keep hands well floured.
Form rope into a knot.
Bake on greased baking sheet in 350° oven until light brown.
Cool and frost with confectioners sugar icing.

title: braised sirloin tip
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add all other ingredients except onion and pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook an additional 45 minutes.
Dilute 2 tablespoons cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Add to meat.
Mix and allow to thicken.
Serve with rice.

title: cranberry banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening with electric mixer in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, blend well.
Add flour, nuts, baking soda and bananas; blend well.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool.

title: big guy sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl or tub so that when you are done you can soak meat in it for about 8 hours, turning over twice. After soaking, place meat in foil and broil or barbecue until done the way you like it.
Baste meat with sauce left or use as meat dip.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs and extract.
Add them last. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cookie owls
directions: Combine shortening
and sugar;	beat until creamy.
Add egg, vanilla and
peanut butter.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in oatmeal.
Divide dough in half.
Shape one half to form an 8-inch
roll.
Add
chocolate
melt
to
remaining dough.	Roll out
chocolate
dough
on
waxed paper to form an 8-inch square. Place roll on chocolate dough.
Wrap chocolate dough around roll. Pinch seams together; wrap in waxed paper. Chill.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Cream together butter, egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder and then pecans.
Using an 8 x 8 pan that has been greased and lined on the bottom with wax paper, bake in a preheated 350° oven until light brown and pulled away from the sides of the pan.
Cut into sticks.

title: peanut butter pie(sugar-free)
directions: Use graham cracker crust or regular pastry shell.
Cream until smooth the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add cream, sweetener and topping.
Freeze pie.
Can be served frozen.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables. Toss lightly.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat with onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper. Drain off grease. Then add rice, tomatoes, tomato sauce and sugar.
Add enough water to cook rice.
Simmer until rice is tender.

title: sugarless banana walnut cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat bananas and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon; add to banana mixture alternately with water, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: cranberry glazed cornish hen
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, mustard, gravy and orange peel.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Sprinkle hens with salt and pepper.
Place on rack with drip pan, skin side down; brush generously with glaze.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn hens over.
Brush with glaze and bake 30 minutes or until runs clear, basting often with glaze.
Serve over wild rice.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix all together.
Do not make jello first, use dry.

title: dirty pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed by box and chill in refrigerator.
Mix whip cream, cream cheese and pudding in an 8-inch pan.
Crumble Oreos in bottom of pan and spread pudding mixture on top.
Crumble more Oreos on top on pudding mixture.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Karo, pecans and vanilla.
Add butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar and onion together for about 5 minutes.
In separate bowl stir bread crumbs into melted butter.
Spread buttered bread crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Add a layer of tomatoes next, then another layer of bread crumbs.
Bake until crumbs are brown.

title: chicken and onion bake
directions: Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup, parsley and poultry seasoning; stir in onions.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake, covered in 350° oven about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Stir sauce; sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with mashed potatoes or hot cooked rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: potato pie o'brien
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring half and half to boil.
Add potatoes.
Cook until half and half is absorbed.
Mix in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Put in oiled pie plate.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour uncovered.

title: 4 layer lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and 1/2 cup chopped nuts and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool very well.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Beat margarine, sugar and egg.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour to make stiff dough.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll out; cut.
Bake at 350° until brown on edges.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Soften the butter and cream cheese.
Cream the butter and cheese together until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
If using pecans, put 1 tablespoon flour over pecans and stir well; set aside.
Add remaining flour, cocoa, salt and vanilla to mixture; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Alternate flour and sour cream, adding to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased and floured 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Also can be baked in loaf pans.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine lime juice, condensed milk and egg yolks in a bowl; beat until mixed.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Chill.
Beat egg whites in mixer bowl at high speed until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread on pie, sealing to edge.
Bake at 450° until browned.
Refrigerate until well chilled before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender, drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place 1/2 the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread 1/2 the cottage cheese mixture over, half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting in squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, applesauce, oil, egg whites and skim milk and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Combine until all ingredients are well blended.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread batter into oiled and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water or juices; chill until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly and serve with Honey Dressing.

title: salmon puff
directions: Beat egg and add milk to mix.
Put in uncovered casserole dish.
Break up salmon and add to mixture.
Add crushed crackers (enough to use up any liquid) and mix mixture.
Press flat.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook salt pork until crisp; drain.
Saute onions in drippings. Pour off fat.
In kettle, combine clam liquid with onions, salt pork, potatoes and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and scalded milk and butter. Cover and set aside 1 or 2 hours.
Just before serving, reheat and serve with crackers.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Mix both beans together with salt, pepper and gravy.
Cook the hamburg; drain the grease.
Mix with bean mixture.
Put in garlic. Make the potatoes.
In cake pan, put potatoes on bottom, then hamburg and bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: herbal cheese spread
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except cream cheese, in a saucepan for 15 minutes.
Place in a processor with cream cheese.
Mix well. Chill several days to ripen.
Serve with crackers, celery sticks or other vegetables.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, hot water and vanilla. Add flour and soda.
Add oatmeal and chips.
(May add chopped nuts if desired.)
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: frosty date balls
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in dates and pecans.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for about 20 minutes or until cookies are set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cajadas de nata
directions: Combine all ingredients adding 1 cup milk first and then gradually adding 2nd cup.
Pour into prepared cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
Brown hamburger.
Add pizza sauce, tomato soup and water; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms. Beat egg and milk, then add to noodles.
In a large greased pan, spread meat mixture, sauce mixture and noodles.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: velvet salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup hot water. Dissolve marshmallows in other cup hot water.
Mix together.
Add pineapple, cream cheese and let cool.
Add salad dressing and whipped cream.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate until set.
Sprinkle top with nuts.

title: frosted date creams
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually add brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Stir in dates and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 14 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and peanut butter.
Add the rest of the ingredients to it, then form into balls.
Press flat with a fork on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; form into bite-size meatballs using a full teaspoon for each. Brown lightly in oil. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, then drain. Combine chili sauce and jelly; pour over meatballs. Heat, stirring occasionally, until jelly is melted. Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce has thickened; baste occasionally.

title: lemon apple-bran salad(makes 4 servings.)
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in apples, celery and grapes.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Just before serving, stir in cereal and spoon onto lettuce leaves if desired.
One half cup serving equals 70 calories.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake chocolate cake (per directions) in 9x13 pan. While still warm, break up into pieces with fork. Break frozen Heath bars into pieces, then crush. Pudding should be made only when ready to layer (do not let it set). In large bowl layer half of cake pieces, then spread half of pudding, half of Cool Whip, then half of crushed Heath bars. Repeat above steps. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: i can't be bothered cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix, straight from box.
Cut butter or margarine into pieces and place on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 60 to 75 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine
first	4 ingredients and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients,
mixing
well.
Add
chopped cranberries and nuts. Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes and cool.
Or use graham cracker crust.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and milk. Add butter to cooked pumpkin, then add to egg mixture, blend well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes until filling is firm.
Cool and decorate with Cool Whip.

title: a sherry wine cake(by mary c. daniels, a friend)
directions: Beat eggs; mix all other ingredients with a spoon and beat with an electric beater for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let cool in pan.

title: date puffs
directions: Stir and cook dates, sugar, margarine until it forms a paste. Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Form into balls and roll into powdered sugar or leave plain.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix milk, pie filling, pineapple and lemon juice.
Let stand overnight.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice cubes in the blender and blend together for 1 minute.
Add ice cubes and blend for 15 seconds.
If desired, garnish frosted glass with orange slices.

title: cranberry crunch cake
directions: Mix. Fold in cranberries. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with marshmallows.
Press into batter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Drizzle with melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: micro cheesy enchiladas
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, Monterey Jack, chilies, egg and seasonings.
Microwave tortillas on High for 30 to 45 seconds or until pliable.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and put it in buns.
Wrap each bun in foil and put in hot oven until insides are hot.

title: summer garden salad
directions: In salad bowl, combine cabbage, zucchini, cucumber, green pepper, green onions and radishes.
Chill.
In small bowl, blend remaining ingredients, except peanuts.
To serve, pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss to coat.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Garnish with slices of zucchini, cucumber, green pepper or radishes, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 to 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: mini quiches
directions: Combine bacon, cheese and onion in bowl.
Spoon 1 1/2 teaspoons into bottom of greased miniature muffin pans.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
