Fill prepared muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool before removing.
Yields 72 appetizers.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and set aside.
Mix salmon with beaten egg and onion until sticky.
Add baking powder and 1/4 cup flour to salmon mixture and stir.
Make patties and roll in 1/4 cup flour.
Fry in Crisco until brown.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk and egg.
Set aside.
Cook onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients (except bacon and pimiento) in a greased casserole dish.
Top with bacon and pimiento.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 chocolate pie crusts.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate (I use a Hershey candy bar).
May be frozen.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Before cake is done, mix sugar and pineapple and bring to a boil for five minutes.
When cake is done, pour pineapple mixture over cake while both are hot.
Cool cake completely.
Mix pudding by directions on box and spread on cake. Cover with whipped topping.
Coconut and nuts may be added on top if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa; stir well.
Add eggs; stir mixture.
Do not beat.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease 3 loaf pans and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until done.
May also use 1 pound coffee cans in place of loaf pans for round loaves.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken (boil); pull off bones.
Line pan with chicken. Mix soup with 3/4 cup chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Melt margarine; add to milk and flour and pour on chicken mixture. Bake at 325° until nicely browned.

title: confetti bites
directions: *Suggestions:
Cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, green onions, cucumber, tomatoes, mushrooms, green pepper and olives.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dirtball cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; set aside.
Mix butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add pudding; mix well.
Crush Oreos and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pudding mixture over Oreo crumbs. Cover top of mixture with crushed Oreo crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: buckaroo cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except vinegar on high for 2 minutes.
Add vinegar and mix for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions and cook, stirring, until transparent.
Add seasoning and water; simmer gently for 5 minutes.

title: fish fillets with herbs
directions: Line baking dish or pan with foil.
Place fish gently in pan and sprinkle with seasonings, butter and lemon juice.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 18 minutes.
Gently lift foil and transfer fillets into serving dish.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: nutty-noodly clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles and nuts so they are evenly coated.
Dip out by teaspoonfuls. Makes 24 clusters.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add oil and eggs.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs and garlic.
Combine cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; mix well.
Dip each breast in butter and coat with bread crumbs mixture.
Roll tightly, starting at narrow end. Secure with toothpick.
Arrange rolls in shallow pan.
Dribble with remaining butter and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into freezer.
Serve while still frozen.
Will keep in freezer for a few weeks.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread mix as directed on package.
Cool and crumble. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Chill before serving.

title: 5 minute peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream and butter.
Let boil for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add the peanut butter chips, marshmallow cream, nuts, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir as quickly as possible, then spread on 2 buttered platters.

title: vegetable broth
directions: Save peelings from fresh vegetables and freeze until you have enough to make a broth.
Peelings and ends of vegetables, such as potatoes, turnips, onions, celery, carrots or other vegetables of your choice.
Add enough water to cover vegetable scraps about 2-inches.
Season with a bay leaf, basil, peppercorns, or any other of your favorite seasonings.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Strain and discard vegetables.
Freeze broth in ice cube trays or freezing jars.
Frozen cubes should be stored in freezer bags. The broth may be used in soups, stews or saute in place of oil.

title: knoedel(german bread dumplings)
directions: Cut off crusts from bottoms and tops of rolls.
Dice rolls with a knife.
Put pieces of rolls in a kettle with eggs and warm milk.
Mix so that roll pieces are moist and stick together. (Mixture shouldn't be soupy, though.)
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: *Oil can be substituted for shortening.
Mix with milk and egg before mixing with dry ingredients.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: jezebel
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and chill.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with Triscuits or wheat wafers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, garlic, onion, peppers and salt 3 hours with crushed ice.
Heat rest and drain cucumbers; bring to a boil. Seal.
Makes 8 1/2 pints.

title: tiramisu(home style)
directions: Lightly butter medium bowl or mold.
Mix Espresso and Kahlua. One at a time, dip 10 ladyfingers into mixture and line bottom and partially up sides of the bowl.
Whip cream until thick.
Beat yolks and sugar over pan of hot water for 4 to 5 minutes, until creamy.
Cool; fold in whipping cream and Mascarpone.
Pour 1/2 Mascarpone mix over ladyfingers; sprinkle with 1/2 the cocoa. Layer remainder of ladyfingers lightly dipped in Espresso mix. Layer remaining ingredients as above.
Cover container carefully with plastic wrap; chill for several hours.
Spoon into sherbet coupes or stemmed glasses to serve 4.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil rapidly for 3 minutes.
Serve warm on ice cream or plain or angel food cake.

title: cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.
Shape level measuring tablespoonful of dough into balls.
Roll in crushed Kellogg's cornflakes cereal.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Top each with cherry quarter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, undrained pineapple and sugar into a bowl. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Drain, then fold in whipping cream and nuts.
Ready to serve.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Put oil in pan and brown onion.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook on low flame.
Stir in garlic.
Add 2 teaspoons water, if getting too brown.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets with zucchini and scallions
directions: Cut each breast in half horizontally.
On hard surface with meat mallet pound breast pieces to 1/4-inch thick.
In plastic bag, mix together flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and shake to coat thoroughly; set aside.
In large frypan, place olive oil and butter and heat to medium-high temperature; add garlic and chicken.
Cook, turning once, about 5 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Reduce heat to medium.
To drippings remaining in same pan, add wine, zucchini, celery, scallions and lemon; cook about 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Return chicken to frypan and cook about 3 minutes or until tender.
Arrange chicken on platter; spoon vegetables and juices over chicken.

title: fruit muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with liners, then combine oats, flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: summer garden special
directions: Place the ingredients on a sheet of
heavy
duty
foil. Wrap up.
Place on outdoor grill on low for
an hour.
No fuss and delicious.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add eggs.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and bananas.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour.
Test with straw to determine if done.
If straw comes out clean, it's ready.
Makes 2 small loaf pans.

title: hopscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Mix marshmallows and chow mein noodles in a large bowl.
Pour butterscotch mixture over the noodles and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let dry or chill until set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple, cantaloupe, honeydew, papaya, mango, kiwi, grapes and strawberries.
Mix bananas, sour cream, brown sugar and lemon juice in blender until smooth.
Add to fruit and gently mix.

title: pink fluff
directions: Mix the ingredients together and chill for a couple of hours before serving.
You may add your favorite chopped nut meats, if desired.

title: grandma grace's cream of tomato soup
directions: Simmer first 6 ingredients for 10 minutes and set aside.
In another pan, melt the butter.
Stir in the flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Slowly stir in tomato mixture.
Good with grated Velveeta cheese sprinkled on top when serving.
Serves 4.

title: italian fish
directions: Rinse fish (do not pat dry) and place it on the bottom of a 5 by 10-inch glass casserole dish.
Slice onion into rings; break up the rings and place all over the fish.
Take four or five of the tomatoes, cut them into thick slices and place tomato layer on top of onion layer.
Pour about 1/2 cup of tomato puree over top of fish and vegetables.
Sprinkle about a teaspoon each of basil and oregano on top.
Salt & pepper to taste.
Lightly sprinkle one or two tablespoons of olive oil on the very top of casserole.
Bake at 350 for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.

title: chocolate cinnamon souffle
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in saucepan.
Add egg yolks, 1/2 cup of sugar, salt, cinnamon and chocolate pieces.
Mix well. Stir constantly over low heat until gelatin dissolves
and chocolate is melted (10 minutes).
Chill in refrigerator until mounds slightly (20 minutes).
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/2 cup of sugar and beat until very stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: red velvet cake icing
directions: Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: dried beef log
directions: Blend cream cheese, parmesan and horseradish, stir in olives and dried beef. Wrap and chill several hours. Roll in snipped beef if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and fold in eggs.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy vegetable-beef soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine water and beef; bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender. Skim off fat (or chill beef and broth until layer of fat forms; remove and discard fat). Remove meat. Measure the cooking liquid; reserve 3 cups of the liquid to use in soup (save remaining cooking liquid for another use). When the meat is cool enough to handle, remove meat form bones; cut meat into bite size pieces. Discard bones.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients with 1/2 soup can of milk. Turn into greased casserole dish. Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caribbean fish fillets
directions: Coarsely chop the scallions.
In a large skillet, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add the scallions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until the garlic begins to brown. Add the crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to medium-low; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: scrapple
directions: Saute onions.
Combine meat, onions and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add seasonings.
Slowly add corn meal, stirring constantly. Cook for approximately 30 minutes.
Pour into a loaf pan and chill until firm.
Cut into thin slices and fry until well browned.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and water in 2-quart glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until caramel colored, stirring twice.

title: spinach ball appetizers
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into balls and freeze.
Bake frozen balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Mix until makes a crumb mixture.
Sprinkle on top of mixture; bake at 325° for about 50 minutes, until light brown.

title: potato frosted beef casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salt water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain well.
While potatoes are boiling.
Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon butter in a large frying pan.
Mix onion and red pepper.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently until onions are limp and lightly brown.
Spoon off excess fat.
Mix in garlic, salt, pepper, vinegar, parsley and bay leaf.
Spread beef mixture in a greased 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole to the drained potatoes. Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter, paprika, nutmeg and milk. Beat with a mixer until smooth.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons more milk, if needed.
Salt to taste.
Spread potato mixture evenly over beef.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until casserole is heated through and top is lightly brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon in large bowl. Add oil and eggs, stirring until ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat!
Stir in vanilla, undrained pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake 23 to 28 minutes at 350°.
Ice between layers and top.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Put in a bowl and cover with cloth. Let rise to double in size (about 2 to 3 hours in oven with light on). Knead a few minutes and divide into 3 loaves. Spray loaf pans with Pam and place 1 loaf in each pan. Let rise in oven (with light on) or any warm, draft free place until double in size. Bake about 23 to 25 minutes in preheated 325° oven.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening well.
Add eggs and cream well. Add flour, oatmeal and vanilla; stir well.
Using a tablespoon, place on a ungreased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: cheesy beef 'n mac bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook beef and onion; spoon
off fat.
Stir in soup, water, pepper, macaroni and
1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole;
top with
remaining
cheese.
Bake
for 25 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.
Serve.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Pour into three 9-inch pie shells (uncooked).	Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, then mix other ingredients, bananas, sifted flour, salt and soda.
Last, add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot fudge brownie cake
directions: Sift flour, 3 1/4 tablespoons cocoa and 2 cups sugar into mixing bowl.
In saucepan, combine 2 sticks margarine and water. Bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix with spoon.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bring to boil remaining margarine, cocoa and milk, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over cake while hot.

title: crab puffs
directions: Rinse and drain crabmeat on paper towel.
Spread mixture on muffin and slice in half.
Cut each half into fourths and arrange on cookie sheet.
Freeze and store in plastic bag.
When ready to serve, broil until puffy and golden brown.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Blend well.
Add raw apples, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well. Spoon into 2 (2 1/2 x 8-inch) loaf pans that have been lined with foil or wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
At holiday time, add candied fruit to make it festive.

title: lemon yogurt pie
directions: Beat yogurt until smooth.
Mix in Cool Whip; pour in crust shell.
Chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add the vinegar and food coloring; beat well.
Sift the flour, soda, salt and cocoa together.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat well.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ground beef chop suey
directions: Cook celery, onion and ground beef in hot fat in a large frypan about 5 minutes until meat begins to brown.
Blend cornstarch with water.
Stir into beef mixture.
Add bouillon cube, soy sauce and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened and clear.
Stir in cabbage.
Cook, covered, about 3 minutes until cabbage is tender but still firm.
Serve on rice.

title: seafood mold
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Let stand 3 minutes to soften. Add boiling water. Stir until gelatin dissolves. Stir in lemon juice, salt, pepper, pepper sauce and mayonnaise until well blended.
Set aside some shrimp for garnish. Chop the rest; stir in crab meat, shrimp and remaining ingredients until well blended.
Turn into mold. Chill 6 hours. Garnish with shrimp, celery and pimiento strips.

title: family chicken
directions: Pound breasts thin with mallet.
Place one slice ham and one slice cheese on chicken breast.
Roll and secure with toothpicks. Dip chicken roll in milk, then in bread crumbs.
Place in lightly oiled baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip m&m's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt the butter in a pan.
While it is melting, combine the brown sugar and granulated sugar in a large bowl.
In another large bowl, combine the flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Add the melted butter to the sugar and stir until completely mixed in.
In a small bowl, slightly beat the eggs.
Add the vanilla to it, mixing it well.
Add the flour mixture in, a little at a time.
Add the chocolate chips or M&M's. Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake about 8 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cheesy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli; set aside.
Combine rice, soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper in 3-quart casserole.
Cook until cheese melts and can be blended easily.
To cheese mixture, add onion, celery, water chestnuts and broccoli.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and place into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie barely shakes in middle.
Let set for at least 1 hour before cutting.

title: graham treats
directions: Mix together with spoon and put in greased mini muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and put them in a Pyrex dish.
Cut potatoes over them, then slice onion over that.
Salt and pepper.
Take soup and put in a separate bowl.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour over the casserole and cover with Reynolds Wrap and cook one hour.

title: vegetable spread or dip
directions: Chop the veggies very fine and dry on a paper towel.
Mix the gelatine and cold water and add the boiling water. Let gelatine cool.
Do not let set hard. Add the mayo and salt to gelatine. Add the veggies. Very good!

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Put into large kettle and add all other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until reduced to thick puree and cabbage is tender and cooked into the meat sauce.
Stores in fridge and freezes well.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in pan.
Add peanut butter and mix well. Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and mix.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in the dressing bottle.
Cut up the vegetables.
Pour dressing mixture over chopped vegetables. Marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours, turning or stirring often.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat everything together except chopped ham or beef, in blender.
Mix 1/2 in cheese and roll ball in the other half.

title: oven cooked deer roast
directions: Begin 36 to 48 hours before you expect to cook.

Place roast in cold water for 24 hours, changing water when very bloody. After soaking in refrigerator for 24 hours, remove from water. Stuff with green onions and garlic by making holes all over roast and stuffing in them.

You pour Italian dressing over roast and soak 12 to 24 hours, turning every few hours. When ready to cook, pour out all but about 2-inches of liquid. Fill pot with water until it covers roast. Cover pot and place in a 350° oven.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours, then add carrots and potatoes. Add water as needed and cook 1 more hour. Serve with rice and enjoy.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Saute celery, onion, carrot and green pepper in butter in large heavy pan.
Add 4 cups broth, tomatoes, curry powder, salt and pepper and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Blend flour with remaining 1/2 cup broth.
Stir gradually into soup.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring frequently.
Serve hot.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix eggs and milk in bowl.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs and milk.
Heat cooking oil in electric skillet.
Put finger under funnel to "stop up" hole.
Put in some batter.
In the center of the skillet, drop batter in a circular motion by taking finger away.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper toweling.
Top with confectioners sugar or syrup.

title: greasy beans
directions: Put in slow cooker for 3 hours. Sprinkle vinegar on when serving (optional).

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti (can add chicken bouillon to water to add flavor).
Dice onion and green pepper and cook in oleo in skillet until tender.
Melt Velveeta cheese in can of Ro-Tel tomatoes in saucepan.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl and add peas, salt, pepper and garlic powder; mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan with cooking spray.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Poke with fork and spread a small can of pineapple over the cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into ball or log.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider and cinnamon stick in a large pan.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Keep hot over low heat. Serves 10.

title: in a hurry italian rice skillet
directions: Brown sausage in 10-inch skillet. Drain and cut up tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Add onion and green beans to sausage.
Cook, stirring 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in rice, tomatoes, liquid and sauce mix.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until most of the liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top, if desired. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grate the cheeses together.
Add the remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix together 5 minutes.
Bake in greased angel food cake pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: orange coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together with a fork until just blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Filling will be slightly puffed and golden brown when done, but will sink slightly when cooled.
Cool on rack completely before serving.

title: glenn's cranberry relish
directions: Grind frozen cranberries, apples and oranges in food grinder. Add drained pineapple and sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Mix together and let set in refrigerator.

title: creole soup
directions: Wash rice; add 3 cups boiling water and boil 30 minutes.
Cook onions in pan with drippings until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and boil 10 minutes; rub through strainer into boiled rice and water.
Add seasoning and sprinkle with parsley.
Add a little chopped green pepper if desired.

title: empanadas
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Brown meat.
Add tomato puree and, if necessary, 1 can water.
Add seasonings.
Cook over low heat for about an hour.
Remove cloves and bay leaves.
Cool.
Mixture must not be watery.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Cut the steak into bite size pieces and brown in the oil in a skillet.
Drain pimentos and mushrooms.
Chop pimentos.
Add these to browned steak.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage with salt until almost done and drain.
In the bottom of a buttered casserole dish, put a layer of crumbs, a layer of cabbage, a layer of cream of celery soup and a layer of grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: asparagus pie
directions: In medium baking dish, place a layer of crumbled saltine crackers.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over crackers.
Layer asparagus, cut in bite size pieces, and liquid over cheese.
Pour cream of mushroom soup evenly over asparagus.
Make another layer of cheese, then a layer of crushed saltines on top.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° until golden brown, but not too dry.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Turn oven to 375°.
Sift and measure 2 cups of flour.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, ginger and ground cloves.
Measure shortening; place in another bowl and beat.
Add 1 cup sugar to shortening and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses and beat.
Add sifted flour mixture and mix together. Make balls of dough and roll in some sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Drop from a tablespoon or make balls on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Roll balls in powdered sugar while they are still warm.

title: mayo biscuits
directions: Mix flour and mayonnaise; add milk slowly.
Fill cupcake pans 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown on top.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add the Crisco, sugar and well beaten egg.
Now add the flour (don't add anymore).
This dough will seem thin; put into the refrigerator for a short while and it will thicken.
When you are ready to use them, take from the refrigerator and put three small balls of dough to make cloverleaf rolls into greased muffin pans.
Do not let rise!
Put them into the oven at once. Bake between 350° and 400°.
Do not use oil for shortening.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, tomatoes, taco seasoning and bread crumbs.
Mix well. Add beef.
Mix well with hands.
Press into loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done. Serves 4.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese at low speed.
Add milk and vanilla until smooth.
Beat in pudding mix, then beat 2 minutes longer until thick and smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip; spoon into baked shell. Chill until top is set.

title: skillet chow mein casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain well.
Stir in celery, rice and soup, water and soy sauce.
Bring to boil. Cover; simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vegetables.
Cook an additional 5 to 8 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Serves 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on pizza pan.
Add sausage, Cheddar cheese and potatoes.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over sausage mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Cut crust off bread and roll flat.
Blend cheese and egg together until workable.
Spread evenly on each slice of bread. Roll 1 asparagus spear on
each
slice.
Use
toothpick to hold together.
Dip in melted
butter.
Place
on
cookie
sheet and freeze.
Remove from freezer and cut
in 3 pieces.
Bake in hot oven.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Trim edges of white bread and slice into halves.
Spread with Cheez Whiz and wrap with half slice of bacon.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: pasta salad and ham
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Combine macaroni and remaining ingredients; toss well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grandma's raw apple cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour with spices and soda.
Then add apples, raisins and coffee.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Combine margarine, syrup, sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until sugar dissolves.
Let cool. Add eggs, vanilla and salt; stir well.
Stir in
1/2 cup of pecans and coconut.
Pour filling into pastry shell and top with remaining 1/2 cup of pecans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pizza burgers(quick and easy miniature pizzas)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off excess grease.
Open hamburger buns and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spoon meat on open buns.
Add 3 slices pepperoni, a few mushrooms and green peppers on buns.
Top with 1 tablespoon pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with remaining buns.
Place under broiler in oven until cheese melts.

title: spice bites
directions: Mix oil with crackers by hand in a 13 x 11-inch pan.
Add dressing mix and spices.
Toss well to coat.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container when cool.

title: chicken dinner in a crock-pot
directions: Place the chicken in a crock-pot. Sprinkle salt and pepper. Add bell pepper, beans and tomatoes. Cover and cook on low setting for 8 hours. Serve with rice.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces. Put broccoli in bottom of a glass casserole or cake pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and milk.
Place chicken pieces in casserole on top of broccoli.
Pour soup-mayonnaise mixture over this and cover with layer of grated cheese and buttered crumbs.
Top with onion rings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture very carefully.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or 3 smaller pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before turning out.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Place on waxed paper on a cookie sheet.
Put in freezer.
Melt chocolate chips and wax over low heat.
After balls are very cold, take from freezer and dip in chocolate using a toothpick.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Fill toothpick holes with remaining chocolate.
Store in a closed container.
Can freeze.

title: shrimp-mushroom dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave all ingredients on High until cheese is melted, about 4 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Serve warm with scoop type chips.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon; add onion.
Drain off grease. Add rest of ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onion thinly.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Place in freezer container and put in freezer. Serve on lettuce leaf as a salad or as a side dish.

title: pumpkin muffins(low-fat)
directions: In a bowl, combine bran, flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt and raisins. Toss to mix. Add pumpkin, eggs, oil and yogurt. Stir just until combined.
Spoon batter into paper lined or nonstick muffin tins. Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes or until firm to the touch.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Line bottom of baking pan with aluminum foil, leaving enough foil to fold over to cover.
Place meat on foil.
Sprinkle soup mix on top.
Spread mushroom soup on top of soup mix.
Fold foil to cover and secure tightly.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Make crust and put 2 teaspoons mustard on crust.
Brown onion in margarine.
Mix other with it.
Put in crust.
Bake at 400° until solid.

title: pepper stuffing
directions: Cook hamburger and onions; drain. Mix with other ingredients. Stuff in green peppers. Top with shredded cheese. Boil peppers for 5 minutes, then stuff. Freeze or cook. Cook 30 minutes at 350°. Unthaw if frozen first. Cut off top of pepper and remove seed before boiling.

title: applesauce bran snack cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, Nabisco 100% Bran, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add Egg Beaters, applesauce, brown sugar and margarine.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in raisins.
Spread batter in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Combine egg yolks and sugar.
Mix until thick and lemon colored.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Stir in milk, vanilla and salt.
Chill. Serve with whipped cream and grated nutmeg, if desired.
Yields 13 1/2 cups.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to boil, let cool.
Add all other ingredients and chill in refrigerator until set.

title: old-fashioned pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a bowl, sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Add shortening and milk. Beat for 2 minutes. Add egg and 2 tablespoons pineapple syrup; beat 2 minutes longer.

title: braised onions(marvelous with duck or goose)
directions: Peel medium to small white onions and cook them whole in a small quantity of lightly salted water.
I allow four small onions or two or three medium ones per person.
Cook until extremely tender, allowing all the water to boil away.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon sugar for every four to six onions, according to size.
Simmer gently until onions are well browned all over, turning often.
Serve with the brown juice.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add the next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 points of dough to top center of chicken mixture.
Twist slightly and seal edges.

title: corn cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 9x13-inch greased pan. Bake at 425 degrees for 25 minutes or until done.

title: jello jam
directions: Cut rhubarb.
Mix with sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Boil 8 minutes.
Add Jell-O; stir, skim if necessary and put into jars.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save liquid.
Spread pineapple in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add pie filling, spreading gently over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pie filling. Top with pecans.

title: chocolate tea bread
directions: In large bowl, combine first 10 ingredients (flour to water); mix.
Beat 1 minute at low speed, then 3 minutes at high speed. Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 7 x 3 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for large pan or 50 minutes for small pans.
Cool 5 minutes before turning out on wire rack.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil sugar, orange rind, cloves and water for 5 minutes. Strain and cool.
Place tea leaves in pot or enamel pan.
Pour over them 8 cups boiling water.
Steep 3 minutes.
Strain.
Mix tea, syrup and fruit juices.
Keep hot until ready to serve.
Do not boil.

title: estella's baked scrod
directions: Oil baking dish and lay serving size pieces of fish on bottom. Sprinkle lemon juice and onion powder over each piece.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over each piece of fish and again dribble lemon juice over each piece.
Sprinkle a little onion powder over each piece again.
Finally dribble melted butter or margarine over each piece.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450°
for 10 minutes and then broil top until golden brown (just a couple of minutes, watch carefully).

title: old fashion butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; blend well.
Gradually add flour, cream of tartar and flavorings; mix well.
Don't overbeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate toffee candy cookies
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with foil.
Place crackers in a single layer.
Combine butter and sugar in medium saucepan.
Heat and stir over medium heat until it boils.
Boil for 3 minutes. Pour over crackers.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Let melt and spread. Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.
Cut into squares or diamonds.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Add a little water and let simmer.
Before serving, add about 1 cup Minute rice and continue simmering.
You might have to add a little more water for the rice.

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes and remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.

title: raised donuts(part i)
directions: First dissolve yeast cake in warm water; set aside.
Beat eggs, then add cooled melted lard; mix.
Add sugar; mix.
Add yeast and warm milk.
Beat with heavy spoon.
Next add half the flour; beat.
Remainder of flour; beat.
Set to raise overnight. When done raising, flour a little.
Roll and shape in doughnuts, then rise again and fry them in fat.

title: cheesy vegetables
directions: Salt and pepper cooked vegetables.
Stir in 1/2 stick oleo and cheese.
Put in buttered 2 1/2-quart dish.

title: easy rhubarb dessert
directions: Cut up and wash the fresh rhubarb and put in pan to boil.
Add water and 3/4 cup sugar (this can vary, depending on how sweet you want your dessert).
Also add the tapioca.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from burner and add red Jell-O.
Stir well, then pour into serving bowl or individual serving dishes. Put in refrigerator until set, then serve with small dab of Cool Whip or a slice of banana.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, sour cream, onion, soup and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix well and serve warm with chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Pour into medium casserole dish, lightly greased with margarine.
Combine soup and half of cheese, milk, mayonnaise, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over broccoli.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Debone chicken, place in large baking dish.
Add cornbread, eggs, onion, celery and seasonings.
Pour chicken broth over mixture and mix well.
Place boiled, sliced eggs on top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown or until firm.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually
add
cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; mix well.

title: tomato chicken and rice
directions: In large skillet, saute rice-vermicelli mix as the package directs.
Stir in 2 cups water, chicken and contents of seasoning packet; bring to boil over high heat.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato and basil.
Cover; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, or until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle or place cheese on top.
Serves 4.

title: lime punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar, water, pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Keep all ingredients very cold.
Add 1/2 gallon pineapple sherbet when ready to serve.
Stir to melt in a punch bowl. Yield:
50 small servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In 2 qt. casserole cook hamburger and onion in microwave covered with paper towel for five minutes on high.
Break up meat; drain fat and add soup.
Spread corn undrained on top.
Cover with enough tater tots to cover the top.
Cook on high for 20 minutes or until tater tots are brown and mixture is bubbly.

title: fruit crescent
directions: In a large bowl, cut cream cheese and butter into flour.
Mix into a smooth ball.
Chill dough for about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough out onto wax paper about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Put 1 teaspoon of the preserves slightly off the center of each square.
Fold dough over to enclose preserves and form a triangle, but don't come quite to the edge with the top flap.
Roll dough toward to point and smooth.
Seal edges.
Bend in ends of rolled dough to give a crescent effect.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Dust with flour.
Brown meat in butter.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Add soup
and parsley.
Cover; cook about 1 hour until meat is tender, stirring occasionally. Gradually blend in sour cream; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: jo jo potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients in a Ziploc bag.
Place potatoes in bag and shake until coated well with mixture.
Place in a glass dish.
Cut up 1 stick of margarine over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken nachos
directions: There are no precise measurements to this recipe; it can be as much as you like.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Cool until syrupy; blend in cranberry sauce. Add lemon juice, sour cream, pineapple and nuts. Chill until set.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in each foil midget cupcake cup.
Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla together.
Pour 1 heaping tablespoon over wafer.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool and top with filling.

title: cranberry orange punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine cranberry juice, lemon juice and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add orange soda and liqueur, if desired.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with orange slices decorated with cloves and cranberries, if desired.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and thawed strawberries.
Pour into serving dish and leave until congealed.

title: veal campagnola
directions: Brown chops in olive oil.
Remove and add onion, mushrooms, green bell pepper;
saute then add spices.
Add chops back to pan. Add wine and boil for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, artichokes, olives, beef broth and simmer for 45 minutes.
Tomatoes should be crushed before adding by squeezing through your hand.

title: red velvet cake and icing
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating vigorously after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Make a paste of cocoa and red food coloring and blend in.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vinegar with last half of buttermilk.
Beat only until smooth.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch or 9-inch cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
When cool, frost with Red Velvet Cake Icing.

title: quick and easy caramel corn
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add brown sugar, then the marshmallows.
Stir until ingredients are blended.
Pour over popped corn, stirring to coat all kernels.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Prepare orange juice, lemonade, and kool-aid according to package directions.
In large pot, combine all 3 with pineapple juice.
Heat 2 c water and 3 1/2 c sugar until boiling and sugar has melted.
Add to juice mixture.
Allow to cool and
then freeze. Makes 2 gallons.
Before serving in punch bowl, pour about 2 c ginger ale over slush.

title: moist cake brownies
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Whisk in cocoa and oil until smooth.
Cook and stir over low heat until cocoa is blended. Remove from the heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well after addition. Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to cocoa mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until the center tests clean from an inserted toothpick.
Cool.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil, add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to oil mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts; mix well.
Spoon batter into an oiled 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
You add the spices to the flour, soda and salt mixture.
This cake will freeze very well.

title: rice and black bean salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Whisk together oil and lime juice in small bowl.
Pour over rice mixture; toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Line large bowl with lettuce; mound salad in bowl.
Garnish with sliced avocado and papaya and serve.
(Should be made several hours ahead or refrigerated overnight for best flavor.)

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put drained pineapple in a casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour; put over pineapple.
Next, cover with cheese, then Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cut butter into pieces and place over top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Before serving, garnish with whipped topping if desired.
Yields 1 (9 inch) pie.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix in order.
Cook in 3 layers at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool before icing.

title: zucchini chicken casserole
directions: Arrange zucchini in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; top with chicken.
Mix soup, milk and nutmeg.
Spread over chicken.
Mix baking mix, cheese and egg until crumbly; sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown chicken; drain.
Use a wok.
Add broccoli, carrots, red pepper and onion.
Saute crisp.
Add dry seasonings:
salt, lemon pepper and garlic salt for 10 minutes.
Make sure vegetables are crisp.
Do not overcook.
Let chicken cool.
Take and add teaspoon paprika.
Boil noodles until done.
Mix chicken, vegetables and noodles together.
Add cream of chicken soup and you have a tasty, quick stir-fry.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix peanut butter and oleo; gradually add sugars, beating until fluffy.
Beat in eggs; add almond extract.
Add the flour sifted with baking powder and stir until well blended.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and add mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sesame spinach salad
directions: Heat sesame seed in large saucepan over medium heat until toasted.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients except spinach.
Cover.
Chill.
Tear and add spinach.
Toss.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar in shallow baking pan.
Mix lightly and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 250° for one hour.

title: cheese crumb baked tomatoes
directions: In a small bowl, mix half the cheese, bread crumbs, herbs and garlic until thoroughly blended. Arrange tomato slices on oiled baking sheet. Top each with some crumb mixture, then with remaining cheese, dividing equally. Bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: ground turkey casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam. Mix all ingredients raw together, except for onions (put on top). Also cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Let set 10 minutes before serving. Serves 2 to 4.

title: mom's cinnamon swirl cake
directions: Prepare cake batter as directed on box.
Put 1/2 of cake batter in Bundt pan.
Combine the remaining dry ingredients.
Make a layer using 1/2 the dry ingredients.
Make another layer using rest of cake batter.
Make the last layer using rest of dry ingredients.
Use knife to marbleize.
Bake, following cake instructions.

title: sweet and sour asparagus
directions: Arrange asparagus on serving dish.
Cook bacon until crisp. Stir in pepper and onion.
Cook 1 minute.
Spoon bacon over asparagus with 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.
Combine vinegar and sugar.
Drizzle over vegetables.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: frozen caramel dessert
directions: Combine melted butter and coconut in skillet and add crushed nuts; stir until golden brown.

title: special potato soup
directions: Cover real well with water and cook until all is done.
If not thick enough, make a paste of flour and add a can of cream.
Then let boil a few more minutes.

title: banana mallow pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine in a skillet; cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until coconut is golden brown.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate to form crust; chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots, nuts, raisins and vanilla, mixing well. Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: nutty cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and vanilla. Mix until well blended. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Stir in nuts.

title: congealed salad
directions: Chill milk.
Beat; add softened cream cheese and beat.
Add juice, then add other ingredients.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream together first six ingredients and spread in a circle on plate.
Top with chili or cocktail sauce.
Sprinkle crab meat on, then parsley.
Chill overnight and serve with crackers.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Mix the brown sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until creamy and thick enough to spread.
Add cream if necessary for spreading.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°. Excellent served over hot rice, using sauce as gravy!

title: seven layer salad
directions: In 2 1/2-quart salad bowl, layer lettuce, mushrooms, onions and peas.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Spread over salad to seal.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Top with bacon and cheese before serving.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli.
Shake ingredients well and pour over separated broccoli.
Marinate at least 24 hours turning frequently.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large pan, brown beef over medium-high heat.
Drain fat. Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into a large roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 25 servings.

title: easy buttermilk custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat and add onion, salt and pepper.
Add 2 cans tomato soup (no water) and oregano.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, buttered.
Put in layers. Grate cheese and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and slowly pour mix through regular funnel in frying pan of deep fat.
Serve topped with confectioners sugar.

title: waffles
directions: Mix ingredients and pour onto preheated, lightly greased waffle maker.

title: yogurt cucumber vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and carefully blend.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with crisp raw vegetables.
Yields 3/4 cup.
Serving size:
2 tablespoons.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and blend in pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground meat in a pot; drain.
Add the chili seasoning, tomato sauce, canned chili and water.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put together in fondue pot and stir to mix.
Keep on low heat and serve with deli chips.
Very good!

title: jello pear salad
directions: Cream cheese and jello together thoroughly.
Add hot liquid and cool to room temperature.
Add pears, nuts and cherries. Chill until syrupy, then add Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator. Makes a large salad.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is bubbly all over top.
Boil and stir over medium heat 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate morsels until completely melted. Stir in pecans.
Drop with 2 teaspoons on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Chill until set.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well, adding milk gradually.
Stir in nuts.
Form into rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Chill 2 hours and slice and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: joan's sweet and salty snack
directions: Mix and spread on Ritz crackers.
(Do not put very much on each cracker.)
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
You can freeze or keep in Tupperware.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve as a dip with crackers or as a spread on pieces of French bread.
Enjoy!

title: cornish hens
directions: Place hens, cut in half, skin side up in a buttered baking dish.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and curry powder together and sprinkle evenly over hens.
Dilute orange juice with the 1/2 cup of water and pour over hens, making sure all skin is moistened. Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove cover and brown skin under broiler.
Serve remaining sauce over hens.

title: "easy do" dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, put in jars.
Mix salt and alum with water and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers.
Add dill and garlic to taste. Seal jars tight.

title: smashing squash
directions: Cook squash until just tender; drain.
Melt butter in large pan; saute garlic.
Add 1/2 bag of stuffing mix.
Add sour cream, grated carrot, onion, soup and squash.
(Onion can be cooked slightly with garlic, if desired.)
Mix well.
Pour into casserole and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake until desired warmth, about 1/2 hour at 350°.
Freezes well.
Can be made easily in the day and refrigerated until time to heat.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch. Stir in milk, chocolate and the 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat, cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return mixture to saucepan; bring to boiling.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in vanilla.
Turn hot pie filling into baked pie shell.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Refrigerate dough for 20 minutes. Roll, cut out and bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: dilled onion rings
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Pack in quart jar.
Combine remaining ingredients, heat and pour over rings.
Cool, cover and store in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Chop cabbage and saute in skillet with 1/2 cup butter until cabbage is brown. Boil noodles while cooking cabbage.
Drain and add 1/4 cup butter.
Mix all together in skillet and salt to taste. Simmer. Serves an army!

title: enchilada dip
directions: Brown ground meat and drain. Add taco seasoning with water to ground beef. Cook rice according to package. Cook beans; add enchilada sauce and cheese. Layer in pan; bean mixture, then beef, then rice, then 1 cup cheese, then sour cream, then remaining cheese, then sprinkle olives.

title: dad's fish batter
directions: Mix well together; dip
fillets in mixture and deep fry for several minutes or until
golden
brown.
Use fish of your choice, either fresh or frozen and thawed.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add corn, salt, pepper and flour.
Beat egg whites; fold into corn mixture.
Fry as pancakes until golden brown.
Serve with bacon and syrup.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash
and boil potatoes until just tender.
Peel, slice and place in baking dish or electric frypan (see below).
Put margarine,
sugar,
water
and lemon juice in small boiler and bring
to
a
boil.
Pour
over potatoes.
Bake in medium oven about 1 hour or until syrup is thick.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in milk for 1/2 hour.
Add all other ingredients, mixing by hand, just until blended.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 14 medium muffins.
(I'm sure my grandmother used lard, but over the years it's been changed to canola oil for health reasons.)

title: sugarless brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat vigorously until well blended. Spread mixture into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into 2 inch squares.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Use basic sourdough as needed to form soft dough. Turn out on floured board and roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and place in greased pan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon chess pie(sometimes referred to as lemon sponge pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Using a large bowl and fork, mix sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: salsa
directions: Cook for 3 to 4 hours, until thick.
Can in quart jars.

title: yum yum cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and oil.
Add eggs and stir.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Stir in pineapple.
Stir in bread.
Pour into prepared 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix gelatin with hot water.
Stir in orange juice.
Cool.
Add oranges and pineapple to mixture.
Pour in long dish.
Chill until firm.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Add ingredients in same order as listed.
Do not stir.
Just make a layer of each item.
Let sit for a couple of hours for better flavor.
Chill and serve.

title: pauline's easy pickles
directions: Drain juice from all 4 jars of sliced dill pickles.
Keep 3 cups of pickle juice.
Add Tabasco sauce to juice; set aside. Layer in a glass pan the pickle slices and sugar until all is layered.
Pour pickle juice mixture over layered pickle slices and sugar.
Let set for 10 hours after sugar is dissolved.
Remove pickle slices to a gallon jar; cover with lid.
Let stand for 1 week to seal in jars.
Don't heat pickles.
Only heat jars and lids to seal. When unsealed, keep in refrigerator.

title: brennan's breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put meat or shrimp on top and then the cheese.
Beat eggs, cream and seasonings together and pour on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a shallow dish.
Dredge chicken breasts in flour mixture; shake off excess.
In a large frying pan, heat butter and vegetable oil over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts.
Cook about 3 minutes on each side, until tender and opaque.
Remove and keep warm.

title: creamy lime fruit and nut salad mold
directions: Empty gelatin into large bowl, add hot water and stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly, stir in milk.
Stir frequently while cooling to make smoother.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and place in a mold.
Chill until firm, about 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add salad oil and eggs.
Fold in the strawberries and nuts, mixing well.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool.
Wrap and leave overnight before cutting.
Do not refrigerate.

title: barbara mandrell cake
directions: Grease two 9-inch cake pans; line with wax paper.
Grease again.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: With electric mixer, combine eggs, sugars, vanilla, milk and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in oats, coconut and pecans.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pie is set and lightly brown.
Top with ice cream and caramel sauce.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: For crust, bake crescent rolls on a pizza pan.
Let cool.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Make dough of first 7 ingredients.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick and spread with 2 to 3 tablespoons of soft butter.
Sprinkle with about 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll tightly. Pinch ends.
Cut into 1 inch slices.
Place on greased pan and bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Add nuts if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Mix in slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken de vine
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer diced chicken over broccoli.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just enough to separate well.
Chop and mix with other ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup Pepperidge Farm crumbs that have been tossed in 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: polynesian meatballs
directions: Make meatballs:
Combine egg, oats, salt, pepper, meat and minced onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs on all sides until no pink shows in center.
Combine peppers, carrots and garlic; cook in oil until tender.
Add sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, bouillon, pineapple (include juice) and 2 cups water.
Add tomatoes.
Bring to a rapid boil for 1 minute.
Mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold water and stir into hot mixture until thick and bubbly.
Just before serving, add cooked meatballs to sauce and stir.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring this to a boil and pour over other ingredients.
Stir liquid up good.
Don't stir whole until ready to serve.
Let stand about 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Combine all ingredients except the sugar, shortening and oats in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in brown sugar and mix well. With a pastry blender, cut in shortening until evenly distributed. Stir in oats and mix well.
Put in a large airtight container and label Oatmeal Cookie Mix. Store in a cool, dry place and use within 10 to 12 weeks.
Makes about 24 cups of mix.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, and 7-Up soda together.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: giant chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Divide mixture into thirds.
Spoon each third onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread mixture to desired diameter.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or lightly browned.
Gently remove and cool on wire racks.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable soup
directions: Cook for 30 minutes after mixture comes to a boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: mock dressing
directions: Saute bread in oleo, butter or shortening; add other ingredients and leftover meat if you have any.
Fry in pan until browned.

title: choucroute garnie(shoo-crewt gar-nee, garnished sauerkraut)
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook bacon and onion.
Drain off fat. Stir the sauerkraut, carrots and sugar into the skillet.
Loosely tie juniper berries, peppercorns, cloves, bay leaf and parsley in cheesecloth bag; bury in center of sauerkraut.
Add broth and wine.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, pushing them into kraut.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Top with meats; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. To serve, discard bag; arrange kraut and potatoes on platter.
Top with meats.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased dish.
Bake at 345° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion. Add soups, green chilies, enchilada sauce and milk or Cheddar cheese soup. Mix. Use oblong cake pan. Cover bottom with mixture (about 2 cups), then 6 tortillas, another layer of meat mixture, 6 tortillas, then rest of meat mixture. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zesty chicken and rice
directions: Drain mushrooms (save juice).
Saut onions in butter. Add salt, pepper, celery, salt and mushroom liquid. Blend in soup; add milk slowly until thickened.

title: "other mama's" tea cakes
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs to sugar/butter mixture. Add cream of tartar to flour; then add flour to other mixture and stir.
Add vanilla; stir.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix altogether.
To make mix richer, you can add 1/3 cup powdered non-dairy creamer or a tablespoon or 2 of malted milk powder.
To serve, place 4 tablespoons of mix in a cup filled with boiling water.
Add marshmallows if desired.

title: kolache
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together, then add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add sour cream, then yeast mixture.
Add flour.
Mix well.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish the macaroni, mushrooms (or olives) and pimiento.
Stir the remaining ingredients over low heat until the cheese melts.
Microwave oven may be used.
Stir cheese mixture into macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until bubbly hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
In a large saucepan, cook pudding as directed on package; stir cake mix (dry) into hot pudding.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into pan; sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts on top. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well and pour in electric ice cream freezer.

title: apple crunch muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and cinnamon into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until fine crumbs form.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to dry ingredients all at once stirring just enough to moisten.
Stir in apples. Spoon batter into paper-lined 2 1/2 inch muffin pan cups filling 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with nut crunch topping and bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter and homemade jelly or jam.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Cook beef; drain.
Add onion, tomatoes, A.1. sauce, ketchup, green peppers and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti; combine beef mixture and spaghetti.
Add soup, salt and pepper. Place in large greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and a small can of mushrooms.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mountain mama mud slide
directions: Mix and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add peanut butter and egg.
Add milk and vanilla.
Then beat in dry ingredients until soft dough forms. Shape into small balls 1-inch in diameter.
Roll balls in bowl of sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Place chocolate kiss on top and press down until cookie cracks.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare as directed on box.
Bake.
While hot, pick holes all over the cake with a fork, making as many holes as possible. While hot, also, pour can of pineapple (undrained) all over top of cake, evenly.
Let cool.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place
washed
cut-up
chicken in skillet.
Add catsup, mustard, salt
and
pepper.
Pour Coke to almost cover.
Cover with lid and
cook
on top of stove slowly for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: congealed salad supreme
directions: Mix jello according to the directions on the package and pour into an 8 x 12 dish.
Allow to slightly congeal.
Drain crushed pineapple, reserve juice.
Add crushed pineapple to jello mixture and return to refrigerator until completely congealed.

title: simple steak supper
directions: Place steak in crock-pot and pour soups over steak.
Cook for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: bake stuffed haddock
directions: Melt margarine in medium size microwave bowl.
Add stack of crushed crackers.
Add garlic powder, lemon juice and pepper.
Mix well.
Place fish in baking dish with shrimp on top.
Put crumb mixture over all.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and broil 5 minutes to brown top.
Squeeze a bit of lemon juice over top and serve.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Spread in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Add chili powder and tomato soup, corn and noodles.
Add half of cheese.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients.
Stir in oil and eggs.
Mix until ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Pour into two lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done in center.
Perforate cake with toothpick and pour reserved strawberry juice over cake.
Let stand overnight before slicing.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sausage casserole for breakfast
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put pieces of bread on bottom, then sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs, 2 1/2 cups of milk and mustard.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix cream of mushroom soup with 3/4 cup of milk.
Pour over all and bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes (uncovered).

title: oriental sweet potatoes
directions: Dip potatoes in Tempura batter.
Drop a few at a time into hot oil.
Deep fry until golden brown; drain.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: banana berry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: six-week muffins
directions: Mix
all
together well.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Place mixture in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crayfish quiche
directions: Begin with a layer of crawfish, layer of Mozzarella cheese, layer of small slices of ham.
Repeat 3 layers.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Beat the eggs well and add the half and half.
Pour over pie and let sit 10 minutes.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle a little nutmeg on each layer.

title: cinnamon butter rolls
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
Roll biscuits flat; put 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon on each flat biscuit.
Place 1 pat butter on top of sugar.
Gather biscuit edges and pinch together and mash down in the middle.
Place in 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Put remaining sugar and cinnamon in pan; dot with remaining butter.
Bake until brown.
Take out of oven and pour can milk over rolls; return to oven and cook down until mixture thickens. Take out; serve warm.
Good luck.
Serves 5 to 10.
I don't know if this recipe has ever been printed; it was my grandmother's.

title: cherry delight
directions: Place the pie filling in a crock-pot. In a large bowl, combine the butter and cake mix until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over filling. Sprinkle walnuts on top. Cover and cook on low setting for 2 to 3 hours. Serve in small bowls. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Remove from broth, reserving broth; cool.
Bone chicken and cut meat into small pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole. On top of chicken, put a layer of onion, half of the chips and cheese; top with remaining chips.
Combine soups, tomatoes and chicken broth; blend well.
Pour over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Put soda in buttermilk.
Cream sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Then add vanilla and mix well.
Grease tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove from pan onto plate.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Mix fruit and nuts together with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter and marshmallows over mixture.
Mix well.
May have to use hands as it is very thick.
Press into two cake pans or a loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: six threes ice cream
directions: Mix together in a mixing bowl, stirring to dissolve sugar. Pour into canister for ice cream freezer.
Let the freezer do its thing according to manufacturers instructions.
Remove ice cream to large bowl and place in refrigerator freezer to solidify. Cover. Serve when partially solid.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and put in shallow baking dish.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and pour over chops.
Add remaining ingredients, sprinkling top with pepper and paprika.
Cover tightly (with foil if cover is not available) and bake in a moderate oven at (350°) for about 1 hour.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: poppy seed lemon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease bottom only of 4 mini loaf pans. In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, milk, 1 cup margarine, eggs, poppy seed, baking powder, salt and sugar. Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl until mixed.
Pour into pans. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar, melted margarine and lemon juice.
Use to glaze bread.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugar.
Beat.
Add egg yolks and beat, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine sour cream, horseradish, garlic, and mustard.
Mix well.
Great served with prime rib.

title: pork or chicken adobo
directions: Salt and Accent sprinkle the meats.
Mix all ingredients and boil until the sauce is almost gone.
Cook on medium-high temperature until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Take 1 stick butter; cook onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock, then drain spaghetti.
Put together in baking dish with other ingredients.
Grate cheese over top and bake until cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: egg macaroni salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add peas, tomato, salad dressing, celery, onion and seasoning.
Chop 5 eggs.
Add and mix lightly.
Chill.
Stir in a small amount of salad dressing, if needed, before serving.
Slice remaining egg and place on top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water 5 minutes - drain.
Place in lightly greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole; add mozzarella cheese & top with marinara or spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese & bake about 5 minutes.

title: basic preparation(the easiest way to cook wild rice.)
directions: Rinse thoroughly and put in a covered baking dish.
Add water and chicken bouillon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Check rice after 1 hours time.
If more water is needed, add water and fluff with a fork.
Continue baking for the additional 1/2 hour.
Rice should be moist, not dry.

title: crab corn chowder
directions: Chop and saute onions in Parkay margarine.
Add minced garlic. Saute all together until onions are translucent.
Add fresh or thawed Snow's frozen crab.
Saute together.
Add dill.
Add creamed corn.
You can hold at this point and just before serving, heat and add heavy cream.
Garnish with thin slice of lemon and sprig of fresh dill.
Serve hot.
If need more, use 2 cans of creamed corn, 2 packages crab and 2 pints of heavy cream.

title: mississippi marinated carrots(copper pennies)
directions: Heat together soup, salad oil, sugar, mustard, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and heat; marinate at least overnight.

title: creamy pea soup
directions: Rinse peas and set aside.
In 6-quart pan, brown bacon. Remove bacon and drain on paper towel.
In bacon fat, brown onion and celery, about 15 minutes.
Add peas, water, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook uncovered if you like a thicker soup.
Stir in half and half.
Heat until hot.
Sprinkle bacon on top.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together the strawberries, eggs and oil.
