Sift the dry ingredients into strawberry mixture; stir to blend thoroughly. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out dry.

title: turkey bake
directions: Brown turkey, onion, sage and soy sauce. Add rice, soup and water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered. Check for dryness and add water if necessary. Add noodles and bake, uncovered, for a few minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator for several hours to stiffen.
Take out and mold before serving.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.
Roll in powdered sugar two times.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, cheese, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli to preceding mixture.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage with meat(malfoof mihshee)
directions: Makes approximately 60.
Boil a large pot of water with 1 tablespoon salt.
Cut all around core of cabbage with a small sharp knife.
Put cabbage in boiling water and separate leaf by leaf.
Cut large leaves into 2 to 3 pieces removing the thick part of the stem and prepare stuffing.
Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and allspice.
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Place 1 tablespoon stuffing on each leaf in log shape.
Begin to roll folding over sides.
Squeeze and place in pot.
In the pot you should have a lamb bone for flavor and the pieces of stem you have trimmed away.
Arrange cabbage rolls in rows and layers, placing slices of garlic in between.
When process is complete, mash 1 clove garlic with 1 teaspoon salt and dried mint.
Pour water over cabbage to just cover.
Bring to a boil.
Add mashed garlic mixture and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Cover with a plate to weigh down.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes on very low heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take Ritz crackers absorbed in butter and make a crust in a baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish; add remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden.

title: party lemonade
directions: Mix sugar and water in a pitcher. Add other ingredients. Stir vigorously with a wooden spoon and pour into tall glasses. Serves 4 people.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pan-fry over low heat until slightly crisp. Flip patties; continue frying until slightly crispy.

title: granny clark's cornbread
directions: Preheat heavy skillet in a 375° oven with 3 tablespoons of oil or bacon drippings.
Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar together.
Set aside.

title: broccoli and macs
directions: Cook pasta to desired texture.
Cut broccoli and garlic; steam until done.
Add broccoli to pasta.
Stir in nuts and dried tomatoes.
Stir in olive oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In food processor, blend pineapple real good.
Add coconut; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit.
This will make a lot of dip so you can freeze half to use another time.

title: nanny's beans
directions: Brown sausage and chopped onions.
Add beans. Put butter beans in last.
Add vinegar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar and stir.
Leave uncovered.
Bake in oven 1 hour or more, the longer the better, at 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground chuck and cook bacon until crisp.
Add cooked, drained bacon and other ingredients to ground chuck.
Add drained beans to mixture and pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: Peel and core the whole apple, then slice across the apple, so as to have rings.
Combine the sugar, water and candy; boil for 3 minutes.
Add the apples; cook until they become transparent. Pack the apples in hot jars; cover with syrup and seal.
Process in boiling water for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese with boiling water. Add cold water. Mix in large Cool Whip. Tear up angel food cake and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour fresh strawberries over angel food cake.
Next, pour Cool Whip-jello mixture over top of strawberries. Sprinkle pecans on top. Refrigerate.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Use an oblong dish; butter or spray bottom.
Beat the eggs with the vanilla and some cinnamon and the milk.
Blend the syrup and the cream cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add both sugars, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Combine all dry ingredients and stir into zucchini mixture.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Add egg, nuts and dates, cook until thick (not too long).
Add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Make into balls and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: old fashion tea cake
directions: Mix the ingredients, sifting in enough flour (about 4 cups) to make a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in medium oven until a golden brown.

title: blueberry breakfast bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg, milk and margarine and stir well.
Add blueberries and mix again.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less.

title: pecan cake filling
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add milk, butter and salt.
Cook over medium heat for approximately 3 to 5 minutes after mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add pecans.
No further cooking is necessary.

title: microwave oven cracker jack
directions: Boil first four ingredients 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and pour over popped corn. Put in sack in microwave 1 minute on High. Shake 1 minute.
Pour on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Break up. Peanuts are optional.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan with oil, or spray with Pam.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 275°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, hot water, corn syrup and vinegar in 3-quart casserole.
Microwave at High 35 to 40 minutes, or until hard crack stage (300° to 310°), when syrup separates into hard, brittle threads when small amount is dropped into cold water, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour syrup over popcorn, stirring to coat.
Quickly shape into balls, using buttered hands. Place on wax paper; cool completely.
Wrap each in plastic wrap.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease well a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Place popped popcorn and peanuts in large well-greased bowl.
Melt butter in large heavy saucepan; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup over popcorn mixture and mix well.
Spread on jelly roll pan. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and separate kernels when cool enough to handle.
Store in tightly covered containers.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Spray "Pam" in glass baking dish. In food processor, chop artichoke hearts and green beans. Add onion and garlic. Then combine all ingredients into baking dish. Add juice from the artichoke hearts and additional bread crumbs (if necessary) to make consistency fairly firm. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned doughnuts
directions: Cream together egg and sugar in a bowl.
Add milk, salt and flavoring; stir.
Add flour until thick. Roll out to 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with
a doughnut cutter.
Drop into hot fryer. Fry until golden brown.
Put 1/4 cup sugar in a bag.
Place about 6 doughnuts at a time into bag and shake to cover with sugar.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crumble cake with hands, then blend ice cream and cake with hands.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into a tube cake pan and freeze.

title: trumpet stew
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, chilies, hominy, corn and beans.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: saucy sausage skillet
directions: Cook ziti for 5 minutes in 3 quarts boiling water.
Stir in kielbasa, broccoli and cauliflower.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes, then drain.

title: "old faithful" ham loaf
directions: Remove all fat and grind together the pork shoulder and ham. Mix eggs, cracker crumbs and milk with ground meat.
Mold into loaf and put in baking dish.
Pour over loaf the tomato soup.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: the best baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash chicken in cold water, sprinkle inside and out with salt.
Uncover.
Put in oven and reduce heat to 375°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in microwave.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise and onion; pour over cooked zucchini;.
Mix in pepper; sprinkle bread crumbs over casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick porcupine meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Make into 6 to 8 meatballs.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Do not use a lid.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: celery plus
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat water, butter, salt and pepper until butter melts.
Add onion, celery leaves, celery and carrots. Simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Stir in oregano.
Simmer uncovered 3 minutes.
Remove celery leaves.
Serve.

title: corn salad
directions: Add Fritos just before serving.
Mix and serve.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix.
Make balls.
Flatten on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix and
store	in an airtight container.
Use 2 tablespoons mixture for each cup of hot water.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar. Add apples, while hot. Sift dry ingredients, then add those along with raisins and nuts to the hot mixture. Add the jam, jelly, preserves or cherries. Put in well-greased and floured pan. Pour in 2 stem pans. Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sizzle burgers
directions: Season hamburger patties with salt and pepper.
Heat butter or vegetable oil in skillet with Worcestershire sauce.
Cook patties in skillet, turning to brown both sides.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, sugars and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make a rich dough using flour, baking powder, lard and milk. Roll like a pie crust and cut into 6 equal parts.
Boil water, sugar, cinnamon and butter together.
Fill each piece of dough with quartered red apples (pared and cored), sugar and cinnamon. Pinch edges together and place in greased baking dish.
Pour boiling mixture over dumpling.
Bake until apples are tender in a 350° oven.

title: canadian noodle salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; chill.
Cut carrots, tomato and Polish pickles into small squares or slices.
Dice onion.
Fry bacon lightly; cool down and cut into small squares.
Put in large bowl.
Add oil, vinegar, mayonnaise and parsley; mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. Preparation time:
45 minutes.

title: tina's fried rice
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Melt butter; scramble eggs.
Add water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and sliced green onions.
Cook about 2 minutes; add 3 or 4 dashes of soy sauce.
Add rice; mix well. Cook on medium heat about 7 to 10 minutes.
Add more soy sauce to taste (about 5 or 6 dashes).
Cook on low heat about 5 minutes. Ready to eat.

title: egg mcmom
directions: Split and toast English muffin. Cut an X in the middle of the bologna and clip edges in 3 or 4 places (to keep from cupping and curling).
Pan-fry in nonstick skillet until lightly browned, turning once.
Place on bottom of muffin.

title: crispies treats
directions: Melt marshmallows, margarine peanut butter and salt in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally until smooth.
Pour over combined cereal and candy, tossing lightly until thoroughly coated.
With greased fingers, gently shape into 1 1/2 inch balls; place on waxed paper and cool to room temperature.
May be pressed lightly into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan and cut into squares when cool.

title: erline's biscuits
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large Tupperware bowl that can be tightly covered.
In another bowl or measuring cup, mix 1/2 cup warm water and yeast.
Let yeast dissolve.
In another bowl, measure 2 cups buttermilk and soda; let dissolve.
Pour yeast-water mixture in Wesson oil; stir until well mixed.
Add to flour mixture.
May use immediately by kneading and rolling on floured board.
Cut and bake as regular biscuits, or cover tightly and keep refrigerated.
This dough will rise.

title: steak in mushroom soup
directions: Cut up steak to serving size.
Put in baking dish. Cover with soup (do not add water).
Cover with lid.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until steak is done.
Serve with baked or mashed potatoes and vegetable.

title: nelda's broccoli dip or salad
directions: Steam broccoli until crunchy; chop fine.
Add crumbled bacon, chopped eggs, lemon juice, mayonnaise and onions; mix well. Refrigerate.
The longer chilled, the better the flavor.

title: baked pot roast with vegetables
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, place beef round rump roast.
Add onion, garlic, Worcestershire, salt, sugar, pepper and water. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Add the parsnip chunks and the lima beans to the Dutch oven and continue baking 1 to 1 1/2 hours more, until the vegetables and the meat are fork-tender, turning the meat occasionally.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix marshmallows and evaporated milk in a bowl and let stand, stirring occasionally.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in 2 cups milk in a double boiler, then cool.
Mix eggs and sugar in a bowl and beat well.
Add the vanilla and evaporated milk.
Add Milky Way mixture and mix well. Pour into 1 gallon freeze container and add enough milk to fill container to within 2 inches of top.
Mix well.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and add to custard slowly.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Keep covered and cool.
Add vanilla.
Line casserole with vanilla wafers.
Put banana slices on top. Continue until all vanilla wafers and banana slices are used. Pour custard over them.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread over custard.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in cold water and cranberry juice. Refrigerate until jelled.
Beat and fold cranberry sauce in Jell-O mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Put warm water in large bowl; add yeast.
Let set until dissolved.
Add cake mix and flour; mix well.
Let rise.
Make like cinnamon rolls.

title: peanut butter chocolate blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cookie mix, contents of peanut butter packet from mix, cocoa, egg, orange peel and orange juice in a large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Shape dough into 36 balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheets, about 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately top with chocolate kiss.
Press down firmly until cookie cracks around edges.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Place soup, cheese and milk in casserole dish with crackers; mix.
Add broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers on top with butter.
Bake at 350° until crackers brown, about 20 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt together in large microwavable bowl.
Place stick of butter in center of bowl. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Add nuts (if desired).
Put in wax paper lined pan and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: chocolate outrageous pie
directions: Using an electric blender, beat the butter or oleo and the cream cheese together until fluffy.
Slowly add the sugar and beat until mixture is creamy and the sugar is dissolved.
Add the melted chocolate and vanilla and blend.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating for 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream and grated chocolate, if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix
together	flour,	soda,
baking
powder,	nutmeg, cinnamon and pecans.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: aunt patsy's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 7 ingredients in large bowl. Mix well, then add flour and powdered sugar.
Mix well again.
Roll into balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: brown 'n serve appetizer
directions: Cut sausage in thirds.
Brown in a 400° oven for 20 minutes. Cook chutney, plum preserves, garlic salt and vinegar until it boils, then simmer for 30 minutes. Add cooked sausage and serve.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Place on low heat until melted.
Pour out and chill.

title: gloria's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and chill. Melt chocolate; dip balls.
Put on waxed paper.
Cool and chill. These can be frozen until needed.

title: lala's chocolate fudge pie
directions: Bring margarine and cocoa to a boil.
Boil 1 minute on low. Remove from heat.
Mix all other ingredients together and add to mixture.
Place in unbaked deep-dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chitlings
directions: Clean chitlings thoroughly.
Wash several times in cool water, removing all gut and excess fat.
Drain a few minutes.
Place chitlings in pot and cover with water.
Add all other ingredients. Bring to a gentle simmer.
Cover and simmer for 4 hours or until tender.
If a pressure cooker is available, cook for 2 hours.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in hot fat until top is bubbly and underside is lightly brown.
Turn over once.

title: easiest yet tortilla casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and green chilies in pan and bring to a slow boil.
Tear tortillas in small pieces.
Add to soup mixture. Add chicken or beef.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon barbecue meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine ground beef, bread, lemon juice, onion, egg, seasoned salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into six small loaves.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350° in an oblong pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients and set aside.
Saute hamburger; drain well and set aside.

title: quiche
directions: Mix.
Will form its own crust during baking.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes in 8-inch greased pan.

title: chicken tetrazzini(make ahead)
directions: Simmer chicken in water, adding salts. When done, remove meat from bones in big pieces.
Reserve 2 1/2 cups broth.
To rest of broth, add water and boil and drain pasta.
Place in baking dish. In skillet, heat 3 tablespoons butter.
Add mushrooms, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Saute until tender. Toss over pasta. Refrigerate covered.

title: heath bar coffee de crocker
directions: Cream together the oleo, brown sugar and flour.
Set aside 1 cup.
Mix together the egg, buttermilk, soda, salt and vanilla. Add to first mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle top with the 1 cup saved mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion seasoned with garlic, salt and pepper until clear.
Soak juice with paper towels and add Spanish rice, chili beans and grated cheese.
Line pan with chips and add ingredients.
Top with cheese and crumbled chips and bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: ashley's dilly beans
directions: Place 1/4 teaspoon red pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 head of dill into each sterilized pint jar.
(I use wide-mouth jars.)
Cut off ends of beans and place vertically into jars.
Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over beans and seal.
Water bath for 10 minutes.
Let them set for about 4 weeks before opening.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, and eggs.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.

title: everybody's super easy hot cheese dip recipe
directions: Drain a little of the juice from the tomatoes.
Mix cheese and tomatoes in double boiler; cook until melted.
Serve with nachos or any Mexican-type chips.

title: panned potatoes and onions
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat margarine in a heavy skillet.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Add potatoes and toss over high heat about 2 minutes until potatoes are browned.
Add water, salt and black pepper.
Continue over high heat about 10 minutes, until liquid has evaporated and potatoes are tender. Pour cream over potatoes and boil 2 to 3 minutes longer, until cream has reduced into a smooth sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.

title: chocolate topping
directions: Combine cocoa with hot water, just enough to make a thick paste.
Add white syrup; mix well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces and spread in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Brown meat and onion; stir in rice, salt and pepper.
In small saucepan, heat soup and water to boiling; pour over the cabbage and meat.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover the dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Fluff lightly with fork before serving.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and extract.
Fill cookie press. Form cookies on ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: In small bowl, stir together flour, parsley, salad dressing mix, margarine and paprika.
Blend in water.
Spread flour mixture over skinned chicken pieces.
Place chicken in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not turn.

title: zucchini bread(two loaves)
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add salad oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Mix and add nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into two (5 x 9-inch) greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco in a bag
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix taco seasoning according to package.
Cut open the corn chips along the side of bag; crush chips in bag.
Put meat, cheese, lettuce and tomatoes on top of crushed chips.
May be topped with sour cream, if liked.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt butter; mix in sugar and Karo syrup until sugar dissolves.
Stir in eggs.
Mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously butter a 9-inch iron skillet.
Melt 4 tablespoons unsalted butter over low heat.
Stir in the brown sugar.
Pour into skillet and distribute evenly across the bottom of the pan.
Place rhubarb in pan and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons granulated sugar.
Set aside.

title: ironstone dressing
directions: In medium saucepan, slowly heat margarine until melted; remove from heat.
Add flour, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, small portion at a time.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring continually.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Add 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese.
Continue to stir and simmer until cheese is completely melted.
Remove and cool.
When cheese sauce has cooled, add alternately portions of oil and vinegar while stirring. To add zest, add garlic clove or 1 tablespoon horseradish.
Chill. Shake before using.
Makes 1 quart.
Also use on open-faced sandwiches or baked potato as topping.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: potato-avocado soup
directions: Wash, peel and cube the potatoes.
Finely chop the onion.
In a soup pot, heat the oil and saute the onion until clear.
Add the potatoes; stir and add the bouillon.
Season with salt and pepper; add 1 tablespoon chopped parsley.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes. Strain and puree the potatoes until smooth; return them to the bouillon and heat again.
If the consistency is too thick, add a little bouillon or water.
If too thin, let the mixture simmer.

title: microwave one bowl fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes until chocolate is almost melted.
Remove.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm and cut into squares.

title: banana coconut cake
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar, beat eggs one at a time.
Add bananas, buttermilk and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and beat into banana mixture to blend.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: layered cranberry mousse mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce until melted.
Stir in cold water.
Pour 2 cups of gelatin mixture into 6 cup mold (sprayed with nonstick cooking spray).
Refrigerate about 45 minutes until set but not firm.
Refrigerate remaining gelatin about 30 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour over gelatin in mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix
together well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° until brown.

title: lemon-almond biscotti
directions: In large bowl, add egg whites, honey, oil and almond extract. Mix.
Add flour, corn meal and baking powder.
Divide into 2. Form each half into 12-inch roll.
Line cookie sheet with parchment paper.
Flatten each roll to 1/2-inch high.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until top is firm to touch.
Remove from oven.
Let cool for 3 minutes.
Use a serrated knife to cut diagonally 1/2-inch thick.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dump all together in large bowl.
Stir until well blended. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan lined with well oiled waxed paper.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean. Turn onto rack.
Remove paper.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add water, apples and nuts. Spread in large pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This keeps well wrapped in foil in the refrigerator for a month or more - two weeks in the cupboard.
Serve with hard sauce, lemon sauce or just powdered sugar.

title: great cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to box directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Punch holes with a wooden spoon in cake.
Pour 1 small sweetened condensed milk in holes, then follow with caramel topping.
Spread on Cool Whip as icing.
Crunch Heath bars and sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar very well (preferably at room temperature).
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each. Sift flour and salt together.
Add alternately with milk; add flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Place in cold oven.
Set at 350° until light goes off; reduce heat to 300°.
Continue cooking for 1 hour 15 minutes or until done. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes before removing.

title: sugar and honey pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a pan.
Mix well.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring until mixture reaches soft stage.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until it starts to thicken.
Stir in pecans; work rapidly.
Pour on wax paper and separate with fork.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch microwavable pie plate.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in pie plate.

Mix ground beef, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, oregano, basil and tomato paste; spoon evenly over top. Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave uncovered on inverted plate on Medium-high (70%) rotating pie plate 1/4 turn every 6 minutes.
(Total cooking time is 18 to 22 minutes.)
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: mom's dessert bananas
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, butter, vinegar and Karo until thickened. Cool slightly.
Roll eight ripe bananas in custard mixture and then roll in crushed peanuts.
Place in dish.
Pour any remaining custard over bananas in dish and sprinkle with crushed peanuts. Serves 8.

title: sausage strata
directions: Day Before:
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Saute sausage and peppers. Drain fat.
Stir in mustard.
Arrange bread in pan.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Beat in milk, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, nutmeg and salt.
Pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: southerner goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion after seasoning with salt (seasoned salt) and pepper.
Add water, beef bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil; add uncooked spaghetti noodles.
Boil until liquid turns saucy, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine hamburger, tomato juice, kidney beans, corn, tomato sauce, taco seasoning and diced onion into a 3-quart saucepan. Cook for 15 minutes, covered.
Stir when necessary.
Garnish with sour cream, shredded cheese and nacho chips.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter and flour.
Press in mini muffin pan.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients; add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Fill greased pound size molds or baking powder can 2/3 full.
Cover tightly and steam 1 1/2 hours.
Makes two 1 pound loaves.

title: squash supreme
directions: Combine squash and onions. Grease casserole with oleo. Cover with stuffing. Pour vegetable mixture and cover again with stuffing. Dot with oleo. Bake at 350° or 375° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13 pan sprayed with Pam.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and syrup in pan.
Cook over low heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add water and again bring to a boil.
Boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: fried rice with ham
directions: Heat oil.
Chop onions.
Fry ham about 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add onions and rice.
Mix well and heat thoroughly.
Add soya sauce to rice and mix well.
Beat eggs and scramble in a different pan.
Then add to rice.
Serve while hot.

title: green rice ring with baby carrots
directions: Boil 4 quarts water. Add salt to water. Add rice gradually and let cook about 20 minutes; tender, but firm. Drain and rinse. Chop spinach in blender or food processor. Make a thick puree; stir into rice. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add the melted butter. Press rice firmly into buttered ring mold. Cover with aluminum foil. Set mold in pan and pour boiling water around it. Bake 20 to 30 minutes until piping hot. Unmold on round platter and fill center with cooked, buttered carrots.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and milk to creamed mixture and mix well.
In a
separate bowl, combine dry ingredients with lemon peel.
Slowly stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan and bake for approximately 30 minutes in a 350 oven, or until bread tests done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put apples in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter together until mixture is crumbly; spread over apples.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° until topping is golden brown.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Bake in 3 layers.
I use temperature on cake mix box.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine cream cheese and peanut butter; beat with an electric mixer until combined.
Add powdered sugar and milk; beat until combined. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into the pie shell.
Cover and chill overnight.
If in hurry, put in freezer for 15 minutes.
If desired, drizzle each serving with chocolate syrup.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, baking soda, vanilla, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
While cake is baking, mix 1 cube margarine, 3/4 cup brown sugar, milk and vanilla in saucepan.
Pour over top of cake while still hot.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Note:
Any frozen or fresh fruit may be used.

title: recipe for a happy child
directions: Mix together and keep warm forever.
Yield:
One happy child.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Mix well.
Add corn slowly, stir until mixture is smooth and soupy. Pour into baking dish, dot with butter all over top.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: pizza bread
directions: Roll thawed bread out (you'll need flour) until it's pretty thin.
Cook sausage and drain.
Sprinkle sausage over bread and then add cheeses.
Roll bread sideways.
You'll have to cut bread in half, because it will be longer than cookie sheet that you have to grease.
Squeeze the ends until closed.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: party punch
directions: Makes 2 recipes for each gallon (without pineapple juice and ginger ale which is added at serving time).

title: peach pie
directions: Combine these ingredients and pour into pie crust. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
